obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line 1
  line `THE RESERVE BANK OF INDIA ACT, 1934`
  line _________
  line `ARRANGEMENT OF SECTIONS`
  line _________
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement.`
  line `2. Definitions.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `I NCORPORATION, CAPITAL, MANAGEMENT AND BUSINESS`
  line `3. Establishment and incorporation of Reserve Bank.`
  line `4. Capital of the Bank.`
  line `5. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `6. Offices, branches and agencies.`
  line `7. Management.`
  line `8. Composition of the Central Board, and term of office of Directors.`
  line `9. Local Boards, their constitution and functions.`
  line `10. Disqualifications of Directors and members of Local Boards.`
  line `11. Removal from and vacation of office.`
  line `12. Casual vacancies and absences.`
  line `13. Meetings of the Central Board.`
  line `14. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `15. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `16. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `17. Business which the Bank may trans act.`
  line `18. Power of direct discount.`
  line `18A. Validity of loan or advance not to be questioned.`
  line `19. Business which the Bank may not transact.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `C ENTRAL BANKING FUNCTIONS`
  line `20. Obligation of the Bank to transact Government business.`
  line `20A. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `21. Bank to have the right to transact Government business in India.`
  line `21A. Bank to transact Government business of States on agreement.`
  line `21B. Effect of agreements made between the Bank and certain States before the 1st November, 1956.`
  line `22. Right to issue bank notes.`
  line `22A. Non - applicability of certain provisions to digital form of bank notes.`
  line `23. Issue Department.`
  line ` Subject to verification and confirmation by the Department.`
