  line 2
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `24. Denominations of notes.`
  line `25. Form of bank notes.`
  line `26. Legal tender character of notes.`
  line `26A. Certain bank notes to cease to be legal tender.`
  line `27. Re - issue notes.`
  line `28. Recovery of notes lost, stolen, mutilated or imperfect.`
  line `28A. Issue of special bank notes and special one rupee notes in certain cases.`
  line `29. Bank exempt from stamp duty on bank notes.`
  line `30. Powers of Central Government to supersede Central Board.`
  line `31. Issue of demand bills and notes.`
  line `32. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `33. Assets of the Issue Department.`
  line `34. Liabilities of Issue Department.`
  line `35. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `36. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `37. Suspension of assets requirements as to foreign securities.`
  line `38. Obligations of Government and the Bank in respect of rupee coin.`
  line `39. Obligation to supply different forms of currency.`
  line `40. Transactions in foreign exchange.`
  line `41A. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `42. Cash reserves of scheduled banks to be kept with the Bank.`
  line `43. Publication of consolidated statement by the Bank.`
  line `43A. Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  line `44. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `45. Appointment of agents.`
  line `CHAPTER IIIA`
  line `C OLLECTION AND FURNISHING OF CREDIT INFORMATION`
  line `45A. Definitions.`
  line `45B. Power of Bank to collect credit information.`
  line `45C. Power to call for returns containing credit information.`
  line `45D. Procedure for furnishing credit information to banking companies.`
  line `45E. Disclosure of information prohibited.`
  line `45F. Certain claims for compensation barred.`
  line `45G. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `CHAPTER III B`
  line `P ROVISIONS RELATING TO NON - BANKING INSTITUTIONS RECEIVING DEPOSITS AND FINANCIAL`
  line INSTITUTIONS
  line `45H. Chapter IIIB not to apply in certain cases.`
