obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `THE RESERVE BANK OF INDIA ACT, 1934`
  line `A CT N O. 2 OF 1934 1`
  line `[6 th March, 1934. ]`
  line `An Act to c onstitute a Reserve Bank of India.`
  line `W HEREAS it is expedient to constitute a Reserve Bank for India to regulate the issue of Bank notes`
  line `and the keeping of reserves with a view to securing monetary stability in 2 [India] and generally to operate`
  line `the currency and credit system of the country to its adv antage;`
  line `3 [A ND WHEREAS it is essential to have a modern monetary policy framework to meet the challenge of`
  line `an increasingly complex economy;`
  line `A ND WHEREAS the primary objective of the monetary policy is to maintain price stability while`
  line `keeping in mind the objective of growth;`
  line `A ND WHEREAS the monetary policy framework in India shall be operated by the Reserve Bank of`
  line India;]
  line `It is hereby enacted as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934.`
  line `4 [( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India 5 ***.]`
  line `( 3 ) This section shall come into force at once, and the remaining provisions of this Act shall come`
  line `into force on such date or dates 6 as the 7 [Central Government] may, by notification in the Gazette of`
  line `India, appoint.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context, —`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `9 [( aii )] “ the Bank ” means the Reserve Bank of India constituted by this Act;`
  line `10 [( aiii )] “ Bank for International Settlements ” means by body corporate established with the said`
  line `name under the law of Switzerland in pursuance of an agreement dated the 20th January, 1930, signed`
  line `at T he Hague;]`
  line `11 [( aiv ) “bank note” means a bank note issued by the Bank, whether in physical or digital form,`
  line `under section 22;]`
  line `( b ) “ the Central Board ” means the Central Board of Directors of the Bank;`
  line ` Subject to verification and confirmation by the Department.`
  line `1. For the functioning of the Reserve Bank in or in relation to Burma, after the separation of that country from India, see the`
  line `M.O. 1937.`
  line `This Act was extended to Berar by Act 4 of 1941; to Goa, Daman and Diu by Reg. 6 of 1962; to Dadra and Nagar H aveli by`
  line `Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and Schedule I (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 1965) and to Lakshadweep by Reg. 8 of 1965, s. 3 and Schedule to the State of`
  line `Sikkim: vide Notification No. S.O. 208 (E), dated 15 - 5 - 1975, Extraordinary, Pt. II, s. 3 ( ii ), p. 1213 and came into forc e in`
  line `Sikkim (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 1976); vide Notification No. S.O. 547 (E), dated 13 - 8 - 1976.`
  line `This Act has been supplemented by Act 28 of 1964.`
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for “British India”.`
  line `3. Subs. by 28 of 2016, s. 220, for paragraphs 2 and 3 (w.e.f. 27 - 6 - 2016).`
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for sub - section (2).`
  line `5. The words “except the State of Jammu and Kashmir” omitted by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
  line `6. Sections 2 to 19, 47, 50 to 52, 55 to 58 and 61 were brought into force on 1st Ja nuary, 1935, see Gazette of India, 1934, Pt. I, p.`
  line `1369, and the other sections on 1st April, 1935, seeibid., 1935, Pt. I, p. 538.`
  line `7. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C”.`
  line `8. Clauses ( a ) and ( ai ) omitted by Act 61 of 1981, s. 61 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 12 - 7 - 1982).`
  line `9. Clause ( aa ) re - lettered as clause ( aii ) by Act 23 of 1965, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 - 3 - 1966).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 2 (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 125 (w.e.f. 30 - 3 - 2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
