obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `1 [ 4. Capital of the Bank. — The capital of the Bank shall be five crores of rupees.]`
  line `5. [ Increase and reduction of share capital. ] — Omitted by the Reserve Bank ( Transfer to Public`
  line `Ownership ) Act, 1948 ( 62 of 1948 ), s. 7 and the Schedule ( w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `6. Offices, branches and agencies. — The Bank shall, as soon as may be, establish offices in`
  line `Bombay, Calcutta, 2 [Delhi and Madras] 3 *** and may establish branches or agenci es in any other place in`
  line `India 4 *** or, with the previous sanction of the 5 [Central Government] elsewhere.`
  line `6 [ 7. Management. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may from time to time give such directions to the`
  line `Bank as it may, after consultation with the Governor of the Bank, consider necessary in the public`
  line interest.
  line `( 2 ) Subject to any such directions, the general superinten dence and direction of the affairs and`
  line `business of the Bank shall be entrusted to a Central Board of Directors which may exercise all powers and`
  line `do all acts and things which may be exercised or done by the Bank.`
  line `7 [( 3 ) Save as otherwise provided in regulati ons made by the Central Board, the Governor and in his`
  line `absence the Deputy Governor nominated by him in his behalf, shall also have powers of general`
  line `superintendence and direction of the affairs and the business of the Bank, and may exercise all powers`
  line `and do all acts and things which may be exercised or done by the Bank.]]`
  line `8. Composition of the Central Board, and term of office of Directors. — 8 [( 1 ) The Central Board`
  line `shall consist of t he following Directors, namely: —`
  line `( a ) a Governor and 9 [not more than four] Deputy Governors to be appointed by the Central`
  line Government;
  line `( b ) four Directors to be nominated by the Central Government, one from each of the four Local`
  line `Boards as constituted by section 9;`
  line `( c ) 10 [ten] Directors to be nominated by the Central Government; an d`
  line `( d ) one Government official to be nominated by the Central Government.]`
  line `( 2 ) The Governor and Deputy Governors shall devote their whole time to the affairs of the Bank, and`
  line `shall receive such salaries and allowances as may be determined by the Central Board, with the approval`
  line `of the 5 [Central Government]:`
  line `11 [Provided that the Central Board may, if in its opinion it is necessary in the public interest so to do,`
  line `permit the Governor or a Deputy Governor to undertake, at the request of the Central Government or any`
  line `State Government, such part - time honorary work, whether related to the purposes of this Act or not, as is`
  line `not likely to interfere with his duties as Governor or Deputy Governor, as the case may be:]`
  line `12 [Provided further that the Central Government may, in consultation with the Bank, appoint a Deputy`
  line `Governor as the Chairman of the National Bank, on such terms and conditions as that Government may`
  line specify.]
  line `( 3 ) A Deputy Governor and the Director nominated under clause ( d ) of subsection ( 1 ) may attend any`
  line `meeting of the Central Board and take part in its deliberations but shall not be entitled to vote:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule, for section 4 (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1947, s. 5, for “Delhi, Madras and Rangoon” (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947).`
  line `3. The words “and a branch in London” omitted by Act 24 of 1955, s. 3 (w.e.f. 8 - 5 - 1955).`
  line `4. The words “or Burma” omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947) which was earlier inserted by the M.O. 1937.`
  line `5. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.”.`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule, for sect ion 7 (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 5, for sub - section ( 3 ) (w.r.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule, for sub - section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 18 of 1964, s. 38 and the Second Schedule, for “th ree” (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 1964).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 38 and the Second Schedule, ibid., for “six” (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 1964).`
  line `11. Added by Act 35 of 1962, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15 - 9 - 1962).`
  line `12. Ins. by Act 61 of 1981, s. 61 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 12 - 7 - 1982).`
