obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `1 [Provided that when the Governor is, for any reason, unable to attend any such meeting, a Deputy`
  line `Governor authorised by him in this behalf in writing m ay vote for him at that meeting.]`
  line `( 4 ) The Governor and a Deputy Governor shall hold office for such term not exceeding five years as`
  line `the 2 [Central Government] may fix when appointing them, and shall be eligible for re - appointment.`
  line `3 [A Director nominated un der clause ( c ) of sub - section ( 1 ) shall 4 *** hold office for a period of four`
  line `years 5 [and 6 [shall be eligible for reappointment:`
  line `Provided that any such Director shall not be appointed for more than two terms, that is, for a`
  line `maximum period of eight years either continuously or intermittently.]] ]`
  line `A Director nominated under clause ( d ) of sub - section ( 1 ) shall hold office during the pleasure of`
  line `the 2 [Central Government.]`
  line `( 5 ) No act or proceeding of the Board shall be questioned on the ground merely of the exi stence of`
  line `any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board.`
  line `7 [ 8 * * * * *`
  line `( 7 ) A retiring Director shall be eligible for re - nomination.]`
  line `9 [ 9. Local Boards, their constitution and functions. — ( 1 ) A Local Board shall be constituted for`
  line `each of the four areas specified in the First Schedule and shall consist of five members to be appointed by`
  line `the Central Government to represent, as far as possible, territorial and economic interests and the interests`
  line `of co - operative and indigenous banks.`
  line `( 2 ) The members of the Local Board shall elect from amongst themselves one person to be the`
  line `chairman of the Board.`
  line `10 [( 3 ) Every member of a Local Board shall hold office for a term of four years and 11 [shall be eligible`
  line `for reappointment:`
  line `Provided that any such member shall not be appointed for more than two terms, that is, for a`
  line `maximum period of eight years either c ontinuously or intermittently]. ]`
  line `( 4 ) A Local Board shall advise the Central Board on such matters as may be generally or specifically`
  line `referred to it and shall perform such duties as the Central Board may delegate to it.]`
  line `10. Disqualifications of Directors and members of Local Boards. — ( 1 ) No person may be a`
  line `Director o r a member of a Local Board who —`
  line `( a ) is a salaried Government official 12 *** 13 ***, or`
  line `( b ) is, or at any time has been, adjudicated an insolvent, or has suspended payment or has`
  line `compounded with his creditors, or`
  line `( c ) is fund lunatic or becomes of unsound mind, or`
  line `( d ) is an officer or employee of any bank, or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 54 o f 1953, s. 2, for the proviso (w.e.f. 30 - 12 - 1953).`
  line `2. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.”.`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule, for second paragraph (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `4. The words, brackets and figure “subject to the provisions of sub - s ection ( 6 )” omitted by Act 18 of 1964, s. 38 and the Second`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 1964).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 4 (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 2013, s. 17 and the Schedule, for “thereafter until his successor shall have been nominated”`
  line `(w.e.f. 18 - 1 - 2013).`
  line `7. Added by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `8. Sub - section ( 6 ) omitted by Act 18 of 1964, s. 38 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 1964).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule, for section 9 (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 5, for sub - section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 4 of 2013, s. 17 and the Schedule, for “thereafter until his successor shall have been appointed and shall b e`
  line `eligible f or reappointment” (w.e.f. 18 - 1 - 2013).`
  line `12. The words “or a salaried official of a State in India” omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  line `13. The words “or Burma” omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947). Earlier inserted by the M.O. 1937.`
