obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `1 [( e ) is a Director of banking company within the meaning of clause ( c ) of section 5 of`
  line `the 2 [Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949)], or of a co - operative bank.]`
  line `( 2 ) No two persons who are partners of the same mercantile firm, or are Directors of the same private`
  line `company, or one of whom is the general agent of or holds a power of procuration from the other, or from`
  line `a mercantile firm of which the other is a partner, may be Directors or members of the same Local Board`
  line `at the same time.`
  line `( 3 ) Nothing in clause ( a ), clause ( d ) or clause ( e ) of sub - section ( 1 ) shall apply to the Governor, or to`
  line `a Deputy Governor or to the Director nominated under clause ( d ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 8.`
  line `11. Removal from and vacation of office. — ( 1 ) The 3 [Central Government] may remove from office`
  line `the Gover nor, or a Deputy Governor or 4 [any other Director or any member of a Local Board]:`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `6 [( 2 ) A Director nominated under clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of sub - section( 1 ) of section 8 shall cease to`
  line `hold office if without leave from the Central Board he absents himself from three consecutive meetings of`
  line `the Board convened under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 13.]`
  line `( 3 ) The 3 [Central Government] shall remove from office any Director, and the Central Board shall`
  line `remove from office any member of a Local B oard, if such Director or member becomes subject to any of`
  line `the disqualifications specified in sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 2 ) of section 10.`
  line `( 4 ) A Director or member of a Local Board removed or ceasing to hold office under the foregoing`
  line `sub - sections sha ll not be eligible for re - appointment either as Director or as member of a Local Board`
  line `until the expiry of the term for which his appointment was made.`
  line `( 5 ) The 7 *** nomination 8 *** as Director or member of a Local Board of any person who is a`
  line `member of 9 [Parliament or the Legislature 10 [of any State]] shall be void, unless within two months of the`
  line `date of his 7 *** nomination 8 *** he ceases to be such member, and if any Director or member of a Local`
  line `Board is elected or nominated as a member of 11 [Parliament or any such Legislature], he shall cease to be`
  line `a Director or member of the Local Board as from the date of such election or nomination, as the case may`
  line be.
  line `( 6 ) A Director may resign his office to the 3 [Central Government], and a member of a Local Board`
  line `may resign his office to the Central Board, and on the acceptance of the resignation the office shall`
  line `become vacant.`
  line `12. Casual vacancies and absences. — ( 1 ) If the Governor or a Deputy Governor by infirmity or`
  line `otherwise is rendered incapable of executing his duties or is absent on leave or otherwise in circumstances`
  line `not involving the vacation of his appointment, the 3 [Central Government] may, after consideration of the`
  line `recommendations made by the Central Board in this behalf, appoint another person to officiat e for him,`
  line `and such person may, notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( d ) or sub - section ( 1 ) of section10, be`
  line `an officer of the Bank.`
  line `12 * * * * *`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1965, s. 3, for clause ( e ) (w.e.f. 1 - 3 - 1966).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 3, for “Banking Companies Act, 1949” (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `3. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.”.`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 6, for “any other Director” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951 ).`
  line `5. The proviso omitted by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid., for sub - section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `7. The word “appointment” omitted by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `8. The words “or election” omitted by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `9. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for certain words.`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 6, for “of a Part A State or a Part C State” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `11. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, fo r “any such Legislature or Council”.`
  line `12. Sub - section ( 2 ) omitted by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
