obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line `( 3 ) Where any casual vacancy in the office of any member of a Local Board occurs 1 *** the Centra l`
  line `Board may nominate thereto any 2 *** person recommended by the 3 [other] members of the Local Board.`
  line `( 4 ) Where any casual vacancy occurs in the office of a Director other than the vacancies provided for`
  line `in sub - section( 1 ), the vacancy shall be filled 4 [by the Central Government].`
  line `( 5 ) A person nominated 5 ***under this section to fill a casual vacancy shall 6 *** hold office for the`
  line `unexpired portion of the term of his predecessor.`
  line `13. Meetings of the Central Board. — ( 1 ) Meetings of the Central Board shall be c onveyed by the`
  line `Governor at least six times in each year and at least once in each quarter.`
  line `( 2 ) Any 7 [four Directors] may require the Governor to convene a meeting of the Central Board at any`
  line `time and the Governor shall forthwith convene a meeting accordingly.`
  line `( 3 ) The Governor, or 8 [if for any reason, he is unable to attend,] the Deputy Governor authorised by`
  line `the Governor under the proviso to sub - section ( 3 ) of section 8 to vote for him shall preside at meetings of`
  line `the Central Board, and, in the eve nt of an equality of votes, shall have a second or casting vote.`
  line `14. [ General meetings ]. — Omitted by the Reserve Bank ( Transfer to Public Ownership ) Act, 1948`
  line `(62 of 1948), s. 7 and the Schedule ( w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `15. [ First constitution of the Central Board ]. — Omitted by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid.`
  line `( w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `16. [ First constitution of local board ]. — Omitted by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `17. Business which the Bank may transact. — The Bank shall be authorised to carry on and transact`
  line `the several kinds of business hereinafter specified, namely: —`
  line `( 1 ) the accepting of money on deposit without interest from, and the collection of money for, 9 ***`
  line `the 10 [Central Government], 11 [ 12 *** the 13 [State] Government 14 ***] 15 *** local authorities, banks`
  line `and any other persons:`
  line `16 [( 1A ) The accepting of money as deposits, repayable with interest, from banks or any other`
  line `person under the Standing Deposit Facility Scheme, as approved by the Central Board, from time to`
  line `time, for the purposes of liquidity management;]`
  line `( 2 ) ( a ) the purchase, sale and rediscount of bills of exchange and promissory notes, 17 [drawn`
  line `on 18 [and payable in India]] and arising out of bona fide commercial or trade transaction bearing two`
  line `or more good signat ures, one of which shall be that of a scheduled bank 19 [or a State co - operative`
  line `bank] 20 [or any financial institution, which is predominantly engaged in the acceptance or discounting`
  line `1. The words “otherwise than by the occurrence of a vacancy in the office of a Director elected by the Local Board” omitted b y`
  line `Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `2. The word “qualified” omitted by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid., for “elected” (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `5. The words “or elected” omitted by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `6. The words, brackets and figure “subject to the proviso contained in sub - section ( 4 )” omitted by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid.`
  line `(w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 18 of 1964, s. 38 and the Second Schedule, for “three Directors” (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 1964).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 24 of 1955, s. 5, for “in his absence” (w.e.f. 8 - 5 - 1955).`
  line `9. The words “the Secretary of State” omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  line `10. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.”.`
  line `11. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “L.G.’s ”.`
  line `12. The words “the Federal Railway Authority” omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  line `13. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for “Provincial”.`
  line `14. The words “the Government of Burma, the Burma Railway Board,” omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s 11 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947).`
  line `15. The words and letter “Part B States” omitted by Act 32 of 1951, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `16. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 135 (w.e.f. 28 - 3 - 2018).`
  line `17. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “drawn on and pay able in India”.`
  line `18. Subs. by Act 11 of 1947, s. 11, for “India or Burma and payable in India or Burma” (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947).`
  line `19. Ins. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `20. Ins. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 6 (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
