  line 13
  line `of bills of exchange and promissory notes and which is approv ed by the Bank in this behalf] 1 ***`
  line `and 2 [maturing, —`
  line `( i ) in the case of bills of exchange and promissory notes arising out of any such transaction`
  line `relating to the export of goods from India, within one hundred and eighty days, and`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, within ninety days,`
  line `from the date of such purchase or rediscount exclusive of days of grace;]`
  line `( b ) the purchase, sale and rediscount of bills of exchange and promissory notes, 3 [drawn 4 [and`
  line `payable in India]] and bearing two or more good signatures, one of which shall be that of a scheduled`
  line `bank 5 [or a 6 [State] co - operative bank] 7 [or any financial institution, which is predominantly engaged`
  line `in the acceptance or discounting of bills of exchange and promissory notes and which is approved by`
  line `the Bank in this behalf] and dra wn or issued for the purpose of 8 [financing agricultural operations] or`
  line `the marketing of crops, and maturing within 9 [fifteen months] from the date of such purchase or`
  line `rediscount, exclusive of days of grace;`
  line `10 * * * * *`
  line `11 [( bb ) the purchase, sale and rediscount of bills of exchange and promissory notes drawn and`
  line `payable in India and bearing two or more good signatures, one of which shall be that of a State co -`
  line `operative bank or a State financial corporation 7 [or any financial institution, which is predo minantly`
  line `engaged in the acceptance or discounting of bills of exchange and promissory notes and which is`
  line `approved by the Bank in this behalf], and drawn or issued for the purpose of financing the production`
  line `or marketing activities of cottage and small - scal e industries approved by the Bank and maturing`
  line `within twelve months from the date of such purchase or rediscount, exclusive of days of grace,`
  line `provided that the payment of the principal and interest of such bills of exchange or promissory notes`
  line `is fully gua ranteed by the State Government;]`
  line `( c ) the purchase, sale and rediscount of bills of exchange and promissory notes 3 [drawn 12 [and`
  line `payable in India]] and bearing the signature of a scheduled bank, 13 *** and issued or drawn for the`
  line `purpose of holding or trading in securities of 14 [the Central Government 15 [or a 6 [State]`
  line `Government]] 16 *** and maturing within ninety days from the date of such purchase or rediscount,`
  line `exclusive of days of grace;`
  line `( 3 ) ( a ) the purchase fr om and sale to scheduled banks 17 *** of 18 [foreign exchange ] 19 ***;`
  line `1. The words “or a Burma s cheduled bank” omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947), which were inserted by M.O.`
  line 1937.
  line `2. Subs. by Act 35 of 1962, s. 3, for “maturing within ninety days from the date of such purchase or re - discount, exclusive of`
  line `days of grace” (w.e.f. 15 - 9 - 1962).`
  line `3. Subs. by M.O. 1937, for “drawn and payable in India”.`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 11 of 1947, s. 11, for “either in India or in Burma and payable either in India or in Burma” (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for “a Burma scheduled bank, a provincial co - operative bank, or a Burma co - operative bank”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947).`
  line `6. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for “Provincial”.`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 6 (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for “financing seasonal agricultural operations” (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 7, for “nine months” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `10. The Explanation omitted by Act 23 of 1965, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1 - 3 - 1966). Earlier added by Act 54 of 1953, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30 - 12 - 1953).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 54 of 1953, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30 - 12 - 1953).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 11 of 1947, s. 11, for “either in India or Burma and payable either in India or in Burma” (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947).`
  line `13. The words “or a Burma scheduled bank” omitted by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947).`
  line `14. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “the Government of India or a L.G.”.`
  line `15. Subs. by Act 11 of 1947, s. 11, for “or a Provincial Government” (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947).`
  line `16. The words “or such securities of Part B States as may be specified in this behalf by the Central Government on the`
  line `recommendation of the Central Board” omitted by Act 32 of 1951, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `17. The words “and Burma scheduled banks” omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947) which was earlier inserted by`
  line `M.O. 1937.`
  line `18. Subs. by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule, for “sterling” (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `19. The words “in amounts of not less than the equivalent of one lakh of rupees” omitted by Act 24 of 1978, s. 4`
  line `(w.e.f. 21 - 7 - 1978).`
