obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line 15
  line `( a ) stocks, funds and securities (other than immovable property) in which a trustee is`
  line `authori s ed to invest trust money by any Act of Parliament 1 [of the United Kingdom] or by any`
  line `law for time being in force in 2 [India] 3 ***;`
  line `( b ) gold or silver or documents of title to the same;`
  line `( c ) such bills of exchange and promissory notes as are eligible for purchase or rediscount by`
  line `the Bank 4 [or as are fully guaranteed as to the repayment of the principal and payment of interest`
  line `by a State Government];`
  line `( d ) promissory notes of any scheduled bank 5 [ 6 [or 7 [State]] co - operative bank], supported by`
  line `documents of title to goods 8 [such documents having been transferred], assigned, or pledged to`
  line `any su ch bank as security for 9 [a loan or advance made] for bona fide commercial or trade`
  line `transactions, or for the purpose of 10 [financing agricultural operations] or the marketing of crops:`
  line `11 [Provided that loans and advances made against the security of bills of exchange and`
  line `promissory notes arising out of any transaction relating to the export of goods from India shall be`
  line `repayable on demand or on the expiry of fixed periods not exceeding one hundred and eighty`
  line days;]
  line `12 [( 4A ) the making to a ny State Financial Corporation 13 ***, of loans and advances repayable on`
  line `the expiry of fixed periods not exceeding eighteen months from the date of such loan or advance,`
  line `against securities of the Central Government or of any State Government, of any maturity, or against`
  line `bonds and debentures issued by that Corporation and guaranteed by the State Government concerned`
  line `and maturing within a period not exceeding eighteen months from the date of such loan or advance:`
  line `14 [Provided that the previous approval of the State Government shal l be obtained for the`
  line `borrowing by the State Financial Corporation and the amount of loans and advances granted to that`
  line `Corporation under this clause shall not, at any time, exceed in the aggregate 15 [twice the paid - up share`
  line `capital] thereof;] ]`
  line `16 [ 17 [ ( 4AA )] the making of annual contributions to the National Rural Credit (Long Term`
  line `Operations) Fund and the National Rural Credit (Stabilisation) Fund established under sections`
  line `42 and 43, respectively, of the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development Ac t, 1981 (61`
  line `of 1981); ]`
  line `18 [ ( 4B ) the making to the Industrial Finance Corporation of India 19 *** of loans and advances, —`
  line `( a ) repayable on demand or on the expiry of fixed periods not exceeding ninety days from the`
  line `date of such loan or advance, against securiti es of the Central Government or of any State`
  line `Government; or`
  line `1. Ins. by the A.O. 1950.`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 2 for “the States” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `3. The words “or Burma” omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947) which was inserted by the M.O. 1937.`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 24 of 1955, s. 6 (w.e.f. 8 - 5 - 1955).`
  line `5. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “or a Provincial co - operative bank”.`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 11 of 1947, s. 11, for “Burma scheduled ban k, provincial co - operative bank or Burma” (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947).`
  line `7. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for “Provincial”.`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 7, for “which have been transferred” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 24 of 1955, s. 6, for “a cash credit or overdr aft granted” (w.e.f. 8 - 5 - 1955).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 6, for “financing seasonal agricultural operations” (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `11. Added by Act 35 of 1962, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15 - 9 - 1962).`
  line `12. In s. by Act 14 of 1960, s. 2 (w.e.f. 30 - 4 - 1960).`
  line `13. The wor ds and figures “established under the State Financial Corporations Act, 1951” omitted by Act 24 of 1978, s. 4 (w.e.f.`
  line `21 - 7 - 1978).`
  line `14. Subs. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 6, for the proviso (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `15. Subs. by Act 81 of 1985, s. 2, for “ninety per cen t. of the paid - up share capital” (w.e.f. 1 - 5 - 1986).`
  line `16. Subs. by Act 61 of 1981, s. 61 and the Second Schedule, for clause ( 4AA ) (w.e.f. 12 - 7 - 1982).`
  line `17. Clause ( 4A ) renumbered and re - lettered as clause ( 4AA ) thereof by Act 14 of 1960, s. 2 (w.e.f. 30 - 4 - 1960). Earlier it was`
  line `inserted by Act 54 of 1953, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30 - 12 - 1953).`
  line `18. Ins. by Act 54 of 1953, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30 - 12 - 1953).`
  line `19. The words and figures “established under the Industrial Finance Corporation Act, 1948” omitted by Act 24 of 1978, s. 4`
  line `(w.e.f. 21 - 7 - 1978).`
