  line 18
  line `( a ) repayable on demand or on the expiry of a fixed period not exceeding ninety days, from the date of`
  line `such loan or advance against the security of stocks, funds and securities (other than immovable property) in`
  line `which a trustee is authorised to invest trust money by any law for the time being in force in India; or`
  line `( b ) against the security of bills of exchange or promissory notes, arising out of bona fide commercial or`
  line `trade transactions bearing two or more good signatures and maturing within five years from the date of`
  line `such loan or advance;]`
  line `1 [( 4K ) the making to the R econstruc tion Bank of loans and advances —`
  line `( a ) repayable on demand or on the expiry of a fixed period not exceeding ninety days, from the date of`
  line `such loan or advance against the security of stocks, funds and securities (other than immovable property) in`
  line `which a trustee is authorised to invest trust money by any law for the time being in force in India; or`
  line `( b ) against the security of bills of exchange or promissory notes, arising out of bona fide`
  line `commercial or trade transactions bearing two or more goods signatures and maturing within five`
  line `years from the date of such loan or advance;]`
  line `2 [( 4L ) the making to the National Bank for Financing Infrastructure and Development or other`
  line `development financial institution of loans and advances —`
  line `( a ) repayable on demand or on the expiry of a fixed period not exceedin g ninety days, from the`
  line `date of such loan or advance against the security of stocks, funds and securities (other than immovable`
  line `property) in which a trustee is authorised to invest trust money by any law for the time being in force`
  line `in India; or`
  line `( b ) against the security of bills of exchange or promissory notes, arising out of bona fide`
  line `commercial or trade transactions bearing two or more good signatures and maturing within five years`
  line `from the date of such loan or advance;]`
  line `( 5 ) the making to the 3 [Central Government] 4 [ 5 *** 6 [and 7 [State] Governments]] of advances`
  line `repayable in each case not later than three months from the date of the making of the advance;`
  line `8 [( 6 ) the issue of demand drafts, telegraphic transfers and other kinds of remittances made`
  line `payable a t its own offices or agencies, the purchase of telegraphic transfers, and the making, issue and`
  line `circulation of bank post bills;]`
  line `9 [( 6A ) dealing in derivatives, and, with the approval of the Central Board, in any other financial`
  line instrument.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, “ derivative ” means an instrument, to be settled at a`
  line `future date, whose value is derived from change in one or a combination of more than one of the`
  line `following underlying, namely: —`
  line `( a ) interest rate,`
  line `( b ) price of securities of the Central Government or a State Government or of such securities`
  line `of a local authority as may be specified in this behalf by the Central Government,`
  line `( c ) price of foreign securities,`
  line `( d ) foreign exchange rate,`
  line `( e ) index of rates or prices,`
  line `( f ) credit rating or credit index,`
  line `( g ) price of gold or silver coins, or gold or silver bullion, or`
  line `( h ) any oth er variable of similar nature;]`
  line `10 * * * * *`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 62 of 1984, s. 71 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 20 - 3 - 1985).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 17 of 2021, s. 47 and the S econd Schedule (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2021).`
  line `3. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.”.`
  line `4. Subs. by ibid., for certain words.`
  line `5. The words “the Federal Railway Authority” omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 11 of 1947, s. 11, for “Provincial Governments, the Government of Burma and the Burma Railway`
  line `Board” (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947).`
  line `7. Subs. by t he A.O. 1950, for “Provincial”.`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 7, for clause ( 6 ) (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 26 of 2006, s. 2 (w.e.f. 9 - 1 - 2007).`
  line `10. Clause ( 7 ) repealed by Act 2 of 1948, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 5 - 1 - 1948).`
