obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line 21
  line `( b ) “ reverse repo ” means an instrument for lending funds by purchasing securities of the`
  line `Central Government or a State Government or of such securities of a local authority as may be`
  line `specified in this behalf by the Central Government or foreign securities, with an agreement to`
  line `resell the said securities on a mutually agreed future date at an agreed price which include s`
  line `interest for the funds lent;]`
  line `1 [( 12B ) the making of loans and advances in foreign currencies to scheduled banks, 2 *** 3 [, the`
  line `Exim Bank], 4 [or 5 [the Reconstruction Bank or the Small Industries Bank]] the Industrial Finance`
  line `Corporation 6 [ the National Bank for Financing Infrastructure and Development or other development`
  line `financial institution, ] any State Financial Corporation and any other financial inst itution as may, on`
  line `the recommendation of the Bank, be approved by the Central Government and on such terms and`
  line `conditions as may be specified by the Central Board in this behalf, against promissory notes of such`
  line `bank or financial institution, as the case m ay be:`
  line `Provided that the borrowing bank or financial institution, as the case may be, furnishes a`
  line `declaratio n in writing to the effect that —`
  line `( a ) it has made loans and advances in foreign currencies for financing international trade or`
  line `for the import of capital goods or for such other purposes as may be approved by the Central`
  line `Government; and`
  line `( b ) that the amount of loans or advances so made and outstanding at any time will not be less`
  line `than the outstanding amount of the loans or advances obtained by it fro m the Bank;]`
  line `7 [( 13 ) the opening of an account with an office outside India of any bank, including a bank`
  line `incorporated in India or the making of an agency agreement with, and the acting as an agent or`
  line `correspondent of, any bank incorporated outside India, o r the principal currency authority of any`
  line `country under the law for the time being in force in that country or any international or regional bank`
  line `or financial institution formed by such principal currency authorities or foreign governments, and the`
  line `investi ng of the funds of the Bank in the shares and securities of any such international or regional`
  line `bank or financial institution or of any other foreign institution as may be approved by the Central`
  line `Board in this behalf;]`
  line `8 [( 13A ) participation in any arrangeme nt for the clearing and settlement of any amounts due from,`
  line `or to, any person or authority on account of the external trade of India with any other country or`
  line `group of countries or of any remittances to, or from, that country or group of countries, includi ng the`
  line `advancing, or receiving, of any amount in any currency in connection therewith, and, for that purpose,`
  line `becoming, with the approval of the Central Government, a member of any international or regional`
  line `clearing union of central banks monetary or other authorities, or being associated with any such`
  line `clearing arrangements, or becoming a member of any body or association formed by central banks,`
  line `monetary or other similar authorities, or being associated with the same in any manner;]`
  line `( 14 ) the borrowing of m oney for a period not exceeding one month for the purposes of the`
  line `business of the Bank, and the giving of security for money so borrowed:`
  line `Provided that no money shall be borrowed under this clause from any person in India 9 *** other`
  line `than a scheduled bank 10 *** or from any person outside India 11 *** other than a bank which is the`
  line `principal currency authority of any country under the law for the time being in force in that country:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 24 of 1978, s. 4 (w.e.f. 21 - 7 - 1978).`
  line `2. The words “the Development Bank” omitted by Act 53 of 2003, s. 12 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 2 - 7 - 2004).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 28 of 1981, s. 40 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1982).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 62 of 1984, s. 71 a nd the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 20 - 3 - 1985).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 39 of 1989, s. 53 and the Second Schedule, for “the Reconstruction Bank” (w.e.f. 7 - 3 - 1990).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 17 of 2021, s. 47 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2021).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 24 of 1978, s. 4, for clause ( 13 ) (w.e.f. 21 - 7 - 1978) which was inserted by the M.O. 1937.`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 44 of 1973, s. 2 (w.r.e.f. 15 - 9 - 1973).`
  line `9. The words “or Burma” omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947) which were earlier inserted by the M.O. 1937.`
  line `9. T he words “or a Burma scheduled bank” omitted by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947) which were earlier inserted by the M.O.`
  line 1937.
  line `10. The words “and Burma” omitted by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947).`
