obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line 23
  line `1 [ 18A. Validity of loan or advance not to be questioned. — Notwithstanding anything to the`
  line `contrary contained in any other l aw for the time being in force, —`
  line `( a ) the validity of any loan or advance granted by the Bank in pursuance of the provisions of this`
  line `Act shall not be called in question merely on the ground of non - compliance with the requirements of`
  line `such other law as aforesaid or of any resolution, contract, memorandum, articles of association or`
  line `other instrument:`
  line `Provided that nothin g in this clause shall render valid any loan or advance obtained by any`
  line `company or co - operative society where such company or co - operative society is not empowered by`
  line `its memorandum to obtain loans or advances;`
  line `( b ) where a loan or advance has been granted under clause ( 3A ) or under clause ( 3B ) or section 17`
  line `or a loan or advance granted under clause ( 3 ) of section 18 by the Bank to any person has been`
  line `applied by such person, wholly or in part, in making a loan or advance to any borr ower, any sum`
  line `received —`
  line `( i ) by the borrowing bank on account of bills of exchange in respect of which the declaration`
  line `under clause ( i ) of the proviso to clause ( 3A ) of section 17 has been furnished or in repayment or`
  line `realisation of the outstanding loans and advances referred to in clause ( ii ) of the said proviso or in`
  line `the proviso to clause ( 3B ) of the said section, or`
  line `( ii ) by the borrowing bank or any other person in repayment or realisation of loans and`
  line `advances granted to a borrower out of funds obtained by it or by him from the B ank under section`
  line 18,
  line `shall be utilised only for the repayment by the borrowing bank or other person, as the case may be, of the`
  line `amounts due to be repaid by it or by him to the Bank, and shall be held by it or by him in trust for the`
  line `Bank, until such time as the amounts are so repaid.]`
  line `19. Business which the Bank may not transact. — Save as otherwise provided in sections 17,`
  line `18, 2 [42] an d 45, the Bank may not —`
  line `( 1 ) engage in trade or otherwise have a direct interest in any commercial, industrial or other`
  line `undertaking except such interest as it may in any way acquire in the course of the satisfaction of any`
  line `of its claims: provided that all such interests shall be dis posed of at the earliest possible moment;`
  line `3 [( 2 ) purchase the shares of any banking company or of any other company, or grant loans upon`
  line `the security of any such shares;]`
  line `( 3 ) advance money on mortgage of, or otherwise on the security of, immovable property or`
  line `documents of title relating thereto, or become the owner of immovable property, except so far as is`
  line `necessary for its own business premises and residences for its officers and servants;`
  line `( 4 ) make loans or advances;`
  line `( 5 ) draw or accept bills payable otherw ise than on demand;`
  line `( 6 ) allow interest on deposits or current accounts.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `C ENTRAL BANKING FUNCTIONS`
  line `20. Obligation of the Bank to transact Government business. — The Bank shall undertake to accept`
  line `monies for account of 4 [ 5 *** the Central Government 6 ***] and to make payments up to the amount`
  line `standing to the credit of 7 [its account], and to carry out 8 [its exchange], remittance and other banking`
  line `operations, including the management of the public debt 9 [of the Union].`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 5 1 of 1974, s. 8 (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 38 of 1956, s. 2 (w.e.f. 6 - 10 - 1956).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 9, for clause ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1951).`
  line `4. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for certain words.`
  line `5. The words “the Secretary of State” omitted by th e A.O. 1950.`
  line `6. The words and letter “and the Governments of Part A States” omitted by Act 37 of 1956, s. 104 (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 104, ibid., for “their accounts respectively” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 104, ibid., for “their exchang e” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
  line `9. Ins. by s. 104, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
