obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line 24
  line `20A. [ Transaction of business for British Military Administration, Burma ]. — Omitted to the`
  line `r epeal of the Ordinance by Act 11 of 1947 which was earlier temporarily inserted by Ordinance 19 of`
  line 1945.
  line `21. Bank to have the right to transact Government business in India. — ( 1 ) The 1 [Central`
  line `Government] 2 *** shall entrust the Bank, on such conditions as may be agreed upon, with all 3 [its]`
  line `money, remittance, exchange and banking transaction s in India, and, in pa rticular, shall deposit free of`
  line `interest all 3 [its] cash balances with the Bank:`
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub - section shall prevent the 1 [Central Government] 4 *** from carrying`
  line `on money transactions at places where the Bank has no branches or agencies, and the 1 [Central`
  line `Government] 2 *** may hold at such places such balances as 5 [it] may require.`
  line `( 2 ) The 1 [Central Government ] 6 *** shall entrust the Bank, on such conditions as may be agreed`
  line `upon, with the management of the public debt and with th e issue of any new loans.`
  line `( 3 ) In the event of any failure to reach agreement on the conditions referred to in this section`
  line `the 1 [Central Government] shall decide what the conditions shall be.`
  line `7 [( 4 ) Any agreement made under this section shall be laid, as so on as may be after it is made, before`
  line Parliament.]
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `9 [ 21A. Bank to transact Government business of States on agreement. — ( 1 ) The Bank may by`
  line `agreement with the Government of any 10 *** State 11 *** undertake —`
  line `( a ) all its money, remittance, exchange and banking transactions in India, including in particular,`
  line `the deposit, free of interest, of all its cash balances with the Bank; and`
  line `( b ) the management of the public debt of, and the issue of any new loans by, that S tate.`
  line `( 2 ) Any Agreement made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line Parliament.]
  line `12 [ 21B. Effect of agreements made between the Bank and certain States before the 1st`
  line `November, 1956. — ( 1 ) Any agreement made under section 21 or section 21A between the Bank and the`
  line `Government of a State specified in the Explanation below and in force immediately before the 1st day of`
  line `November, 1956, shall, as from that day have effect as if it were an agree ment made on that day under`
  line `section 21A between the Bank and the Government of the corresponding State subject to such`
  line `modifications, if any, being of a character not affecting the general operation of the agreement, as may be`
  line `agreed upon between the Bank and the Government of the corresponding State, or in default of such`
  line `agreement, as may be made therein by order of the Central Government.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub - section “ corresponding State ’ ’ means, —`
  line `( a ) in relation to the agreement between the Bank and the State of Andhra, the State of Andhra`
  line Pradesh;
  line `1. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.`
  line `2. The words “and the State Governments” omitted by Act 37 of 1956, s. 104 (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 104, ibid., for “their” (w.e.f. 1 - 1 1 - 1956).`
  line `4. The words “or any State Government” omitted by s. 104, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 104, ibid., for “they” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
  line `6. The words “and each State Government” omitted by s. 104, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 104, ibid. for sub - section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
  line `8. Sub - section ( 5 ) omitted by s. 104, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956) which was inserted by Act 32 of 1951, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `10. The wor d and letter “Part B” omitted by Act 37 of 1956, s. 104 (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
  line `11. The words “(including the autonomous State of Meghalaya)” omitted by Act 81 of 1971, s. 72 (w.e.f. 21 - 1 - 1972) which was`
  line `earlier inserted by Act 55 of 1969, s. 75 (w.e.f. 2 - 4 - 19 70).`
  line `12. Ins. by Act 37 of 1956, s. 104 (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
