obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line 25
  line `( b ) in relation to the agreement between the Bank and any other Part A State as it existed before`
  line `the 1st day of November, 1956, the State with the same name; and`
  line `( c ) in relation to the agreement between t he Bank and the Part B State of Mysore or Travancore -`
  line `Cochin as it existed before the 1st day of November, 1956, the State of Mysore of Kerala`
  line respectively.
  line `( 2 ) Any agreement made under section 21A between the Bank and the Government of the Part B`
  line `State of Hyderabad, Madhya Bharat or Saurashtra shall be deemed to have terminated on the 31st day of`
  line `October, 1956.]`
  line `22. Right to issue bank notes. — ( 1 ) The Bank shall have the sole right to issue bank notes`
  line `in 1 [India], and may, for a period which shall be fixed by the 2 [Central Government] on the`
  line `recommendation of the Central Board, issue currency notes of the Government of India supplied to it by`
  line `the 2 [Central Government], and the provisions of this Act applicable to bank notes shall, unless a contrary`
  line `intention appears, apply to all currency notes of the Government of India issued either by the 2 [Central`
  line `Government] or by the Bank in like manner as if such currency notes were bank notes, and references in`
  line `this Act to bank notes shall be construed accordingly.`
  line `( 2 ) On and from the date on which this Chapter comes into force the 2 [Central Government] shall not`
  line `issue any currency notes.`
  line `3 [ 22A. Non - applicability of certain provisions to digital form of bank notes. — Nothing contained`
  line `in sections 24, 25, 27, 28 and 39 shall apply to the bank notes issued in digital form by the Bank.]`
  line `23. Issue Department. — ( 1 ) The issue of bank notes shall be conducted by the Bank in an Issue`
  line `Department which shall be separated and kept wholly distinct from the Banking Department, and the`
  line `assets of the Issue Department shall not be subject to any liability other than the liabilities of the Issue`
  line `Department as hereinafter defined in section 34.`
  line `( 2 ) The Issue Department shall not issue bank notes to the Banking Department or to any other person`
  line `except in exchange for other bank notes or for such coin, bullion or securities as are permitted by this Act`
  line `to form part of the Reserve.`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 [ 24. Denominations of notes. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub - section ( 2 ) bank notes shall be`
  line `of the denominational value to two rupees, five rupees, ten rupees, twenty rupees, fifty rupees, one`
  line `hundred rupees, five hundred rupees, one thousand rupees, five thousand rupees and ten thousand rupees`
  line `or of such other denominational values, not exceeding ten thousand rupees, as the Central Government`
  line `may, on the recommendation of the Central Board, specify in this behalf.`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government may, on the recommendation of the Central Board, direct the non - issue`
  line `or the discontinuance of iss ue of bank notes of such denominational values as it may specify in this`
  line behalf.]
  line `25. Form of bank notes. — The design, form the material of bank notes shall be such as may be`
  line `approved by the 2 [Central Government] after consideration of the recommendations m ade by the Central`
  line Board.
  line `26. Legal tender character of notes. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of subsection ( 2 ), every bank`
  line `note shall be legal tender at any place in 1 [India] in payment, or on account for the amount expressed`
  line `therein, and shall be guaranteed by the 2 [Central Government].`
  line `( 2 ) On recommendation of the Central Board the 2 [Central Government] may, by notification in the`
  line `Gazette of India, declare that, with effect from such date as may be specified in the notification, any series`
  line `of bank notes of any denomination shall cease to be legal tender 6 [save at such office or agency of the`
  line `Bank and to such extent as may be specified in the notification].`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 2, for “the States” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `2. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.”.`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 125 (w.e.f. 30 - 3 - 2022).`
  line `4. Sub - section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947) which was inserted by the M.O. 1937.`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 58 of 1968, s. 25, for section 24 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 1969).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 13, for “save at an office or agency of the Bank” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
