obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line 26
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [ 26A. Certain bank notes to cease to be legal tender. — Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 26, no bank note of the denominational value of five hundred rupees, one thousand rupees or ten`
  line `thousand rupees issued before the 13th day of January, 1946, shall be legal tender in payment or on`
  line `account for th e amount expressed therein.]`
  line `27. Re - issue notes. — The Bank shall not re - issue bank notes which are torn, defaced or excessively`
  line spoiled.
  line `28. Recovery of notes lost, stolen, mutilated or imperfect. — 3 *** Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any enactment or rule of law to the contrary, no person shall of right be entitled to recover`
  line `from the 4 [Central Government] or the Bank, the value of any lost, stolen, mutilated or imperfect currency`
  line `note of the Government of India or bank note:`
  line `Provided that the Bank ma y, with the previous sanction of the 4 [Central Government], prescribed the`
  line `circumstances in and the conditions and limitations subject to which the value of such currency notes or`
  line `bank notes may be refunded as of grace and the rules made under this proviso shall be laid on the`
  line `table 5 *** of 6 [ Parliament].`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `8 [ 28A. Issue of special bank notes and special one rupee notes in certain cases. — ( 1 ) For the`
  line `purpose of controlling the circulation of bank notes without India, the Bank may, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other provision of this Act, issue bank notes of such design, form and material`
  line `as may be approved under sub - section ( 3 ) (hereinafter in this section referred to as special bank notes) of`
  line `the denominational values of five rupees, ten rupees and one hundred rupee s.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purpose of controlling the circulation of Government of India one rupee notes without`
  line `India, the Central Government may, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this`
  line `Act or in the Currency Ordinance, 1940 (Ord. 4 of 1940 ) issue Government of India notes of the`
  line `denominational value of one rupee of such design, form and material as may be adopted under sub -`
  line `section ( 3 ) (hereinafter in this section referred to as special one rupee notes).`
  line `( 3 ) The design, form and material of the special bank notes shall be such as may be approved by the`
  line `Central Government after consideration of the recommendations made by the Governor and of the special`
  line `one rupee notes shall be such as the Central Government may think fit to adopt.`
  line `( 4 ) Neither the special bank notes not the special one rupee notes shall be legal tender in India.`
  line `( 5 ) The special one rupee note shall be deemed to be included in the expression “ rupee coin ” for all`
  line `the purposes of this Act except section 39, but shall be deemed not to be a currency note for any of the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 6 ) Where a special bank note is on its face expressed to be payable at a specified office or branch of`
  line `the Bank, the obligation imposed by section 39 shall be only on the specified office or bran ch and,`
  line `further, shall be subject to such regulations as may be made under this section.`
  line `( 7 ) The Bank may, with the previous sanction of the Central Government, make regulations to`
  line `provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or convenient for the purpose of giving effect to`
  line `the provisions of this section, and, in particular, the manner in which, and the conditions or limitations`
  line `subject to which —`
  line `1. Sub - section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947) which was inserted by the M.O. 1937.`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1956).`
  line `3. The brackets and figure “( 1 )” omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947) which was inserted by the M.O. 1937.`
  line `4. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.”.`
  line `5. The words “of both Houses” omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  line `6. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for “the Central Legislature”.`
  line `7. Sub - section ( 2 ) omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947) which was inserted by the M.O. 1937.`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 14 of 1959, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 - 5 - 1959).`
