obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line 27
  line `( i ) bank notes and one rupee notes in circulation in any country outside India may be replaced by`
  line `s pecial notes issued under this section;`
  line `( ii ) any such special notes may be exchanged for any other bank notes or one rupee notes.]`
  line `29. Bank exempt from stamp duty on bank notes. — The Bank shall not be liable to the payment of`
  line `any stamp duty under the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899) in respect of bank notes 1 *** issued by it.`
  line `30. Powers of Central Government to supersede Central Board. — ( 1 ) If in the opinion of`
  line `the 2 [Central Government] the Bank fails to carry out any of the obligations imposed on it by or under this`
  line `Act 3 *** 4 [the Central Government] may, by notification in the Gazette of India, declare the Central`
  line `Board to be superseded, and thereafter the general superintendence and direction of the affairs of the`
  line `Bank shall be entrusted to such agency as the 2 [Central Government] may determine, and such agency`
  line `may exercise the powers and do all acts and things which may be exercised or done by the Central Board`
  line `under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) When action is taken under this section the 2 [Central Government] shall cau se a full report of the`
  line `circumstances leading to such action and of the action taken to be laid before 5 [Parliament] at the earliest`
  line `possible opportunity and in any case within three months from the issue of the notification superseding`
  line `the Board.`
  line `31. Issue of demand bills and notes. — 6 [( 1 )] No person in 7 [India] other than the Bank, or, as`
  line `expressly authori s ed by this Act the 2 [Central Government] shall draw, accept, make or issue any bill of`
  line `exchange, hundi, promissory note or engagement for the payme nt of money payable to bearer on demand,`
  line `or borrow, owe or take up any sum or sums of money on the bills, hundis or notes payable to bearer on`
  line `demand of any such person:`
  line `Provided that cheques or drafts, including hundis, payable to bearer on demand or othe rwise may be`
  line `drawn on a person ’ s account with a banker, shroff or agent.`
  line `8 [( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881, (26 of 1881) no`
  line `person in 7 [India] other than the Bank or, as expressly authorised by this Act, the Central Government`
  line `shall make or issue any promissory note expressed to be payable to the bearer of the instrument.]`
  line `9 [( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the Central Government may authorise any`
  line `scheduled bank to issu e electoral bond.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub - section, “ electroal bond ” means a bond issued by any`
  line `scheduled bank under the scheme as may be notified by the Central Government.]`
  line `32. [ Penalty ]. — Omitted by the Reserve Bank of India ( Amendment ) Act, 1974 (51 of 1974), s.`
  line `9 ( w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `33. Assets of the Issue Department. — ( 1 ) The assets of the Issue Department shall consist of gold`
  line `coin, gold bullion, 10 [foreign securities], rupee coin and rupee securities to such aggregate amount as is`
  line `not less than the total of the liabilities of the Issue Department as hereinafter defined.`
  line `11 [( 2 ) The aggregate value of the gold coin, gold bullion and foreign securities held as assets and the`
  line `aggregate value of the gold coin and gold bullion so held shall not at any time be less than two hundred`
  line `crores of rupees and one hundred and fifteen crores of rupees, respectively.]`
  line `1. The words “or Burma notes” omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947) which was earlier inserted by the M.O. 1937.`
  line `2. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.”.`
  line `3. The words “or by or under the law of Burma” omitted by Act 11 of 1947, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947) which was earlier inserted by`
  line `the M.O. 1937.`
  line `4. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “he”.`
  line `5. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for “the Central Legislature”.`
  line `6. S ection 31 renumbered as sub - section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 23 of 1946, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10 - 11 - 1946).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 2, for “the States” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `8. Added by Act 23 of 1946, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10 - 11 - 1946).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 134 (w.e. f. 1 - 4 - 2017).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule, for “sterling securities” (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 48 of 1957, s. 2, for sub - section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 31 - 10 - 1957).`
