obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line 28
  line `1 [( 3 ) The remainder of the assets shall be held in rupee coin, Government of India rupee securities of`
  line `any maturity, promissory notes dra wn by the National Bank for any loans or advances under clause ( 4E )`
  line `of section 17 and such bills of exchange and promissory notes payable in India as are eligible for`
  line `purchase by the Bank under sub - clause ( a ) or sub - clause ( b ) or sub - clause ( bb ) of clause ( 2 ) of section 17`
  line `or under clause ( 1 ) of section 18.]`
  line `( 4 ) For the purposes of this section, gold coin the gold bullion shall be valu ed at 2 [a price not`
  line `exceeding the international market pri ce for the time being obtaining ], rupee coin shall be valued at it s`
  line `face value, and securities shall be valued 3 [at rates not exceeding the market rates] for the time being`
  line obtaining.
  line `( 5 ) Of the gold coin and gold bullion held as assets, not less than seventeen - twentieths shall be held`
  line `in 4 [India], and all gold coin and gold bullion held as assets shall be held in the custody of the Bank or its`
  line `agencies:`
  line `Provided that gold belonging to the Bank which is in any other bank or in any mint or treasury or in`
  line `transit may be reckoned as part of the assets.`
  line `5 [( 6 ) For the purposes of this section, the foreign securities which may be held as part of the assets`
  line `shall be —`
  line `( i ) securities of the following kinds payable in the currency of any foreign country which is a`
  line `member of the Inter national Monetary Fund, namely: —`
  line `( a ) balances with the bank which is the principal currency authority of that foreign country`
  line `and any other balances or securities in foreign currency maintained with or issued by the`
  line `International Monetary Fund, the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development, th e`
  line `International Development Association or the International Finance Corporation 6 [or Asian`
  line `Development Bank] or the Bank for International Settlements or 7 [any banking or financial`
  line `institution 8 [approved] by the Central Government] in this behalf provided that they are repayable`
  line `within a 9 [period of ten years];`
  line `( b ) bills of exchange bearing two or more good signatures and drawn on and payable at any`
  line `place in that foreign country and having a maturity not exceeding ninety days; and`
  line `( c ) Government securities of that foreign country maturing 10 [within ten years];`
  line `( ii ) any drawing rights representing a liability of the International Monetary Fund. ]`
  line `34. Liabilities of Issue Department. — ( 1 ) The Liabilities of the Issue Department shall be an amount`
  line `equal to the total of the amount of the currency notes of the Government of India and bank notes for the`
  line `time being in circulation.`
  line `11 * * * * *`
  line `12 * * * * *`
  line `35. [ Initial assets and liabilities ]. — Omitted by the Reserve Bank ( Transfer to Public Ownership )`
  line `Act, 1948 ( 62 of 1948 ), s. 7 and the Schedule ( w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 61 of 1981, s. 61 and the Second Schedule, for sub - se ction ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 12 - 7 - 1982).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 1991, s. 2, for “0.118489 grammes of fine gold per rupee” (w.e.f. 15 - 10 - 1990).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 58 of 1968, s. 26, for “at the market rate” (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 1969).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 2, for “the Stat es” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 10, for sub - section ( 6 ) (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 24 of 1978, s. 6 (w.e.f. 21 - 7 - 1978).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for “any commercial bank notified by the Central Government” (w.e.f. 21 - 7 - 1978).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 4, for “notified” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 1984).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 24 of 1978, s. 6, for “period of five years” (w.e.f. 21 - 7 - 198).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for “within five years” (w.e.f. 21 - 7 - 198).`
  line `11. Sub - section ( 2 ) omitted by Act 55 of 1963, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 1964).`
  line `12. Sub - section ( 3 ) omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 1964) which was earlier inserted by the M.O. 1937.`
