obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line 29
  line `36. [ Method of dealing with fluctuations in rupee coin assets ]. — Omitted by the Banking Laws`
  line `( Miscellaneous Provisions ) Act, 1963 ( 55 of 1963 ), s. 3 ( w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 1964).`
  line `1 [ 37. Suspension of assets requirements as to foreign securities. — Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the foregoing provisions, the Bank may, with the previous sanction of the Central`
  line `Government, for periods not exceeding six months in the first instance, which may, with th e like sanction,`
  line `be extended from time to time by period not exceeding three months at a time, hold as assets foreign`
  line `securities of less amount in value than that required by sub - section ( 2 ) of section 33.`
  line `2 * * * * *]`
  line `38. Obligations of Government and the Bank in respect of rupee coin. — The 3 [Central`
  line `Government ] shall undertake not 4 *** to put into circulation any ru pees, except through the Bank, 5 ***`
  line `and the Bank shall undertake not to dispose of rupee coin otherwise than f or the purposes of`
  line `circulation 6 ***.`
  line `39. Obligation to supply different forms of currency. — ( 1 ) The Bank shall issue rupee coin on`
  line `demand in exchange for bank notes and currency notes of the Government of India and shall issue`
  line `currency notes or bank notes on demand in exchange for coin which is legal tender under the Indian`
  line `Coinage Act, 1906 (3 of 1906).`
  line `( 2 ) The Bank shall, in exchange for currency notes or bank notes of 7 [two] rupees or upwards, supply`
  line `currency notes or bank notes of lower value or other c oins which are legal tender under the Indian`
  line `Coinage Act, 1906 (3 of 1906), in such quantities as may, in the opinion of the Bank, be required for`
  line `circulation; and the 3 [Central Government] shall supply such coins to the Bank on demand. If`
  line `the 3 [Central Government] at any time fails to supply such coins, the Bank shall be released from its`
  line `obligations to supply them to the public.`
  line `8 [ 40. Transactions in foreign exchange. — The Bank shall sell to or buy from any authori s ed person`
  line `who makes a demand in that be half at its office in Bombay, Calcutta, Delhi or Madras 9 [or at such or its`
  line `branches as the Central Government may, by order determine], foreign exchange at such rates of`
  line `exchange and on such conditions as the Central Government may from time to time by ge neral or special`
  line `order determine, having regard so far as rates of exchange are concerned to its obligations to the`
  line `International Monetary Fund:`
  line `Provided that no person shall be entitled to demand to buy or sell foreign exchange of a value less`
  line `than two la khs of rupees.`
  line `Explanation. — In the section “ authori s ed person ” means a person who is entitled by or under`
  line `the 10 [Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973)], to buy, or as the case may be, sell, the`
  line `foreign exchange to which his demand relates.]`
  line `41A. [ Obligation to provide remittance between India and Burma ]. — Omitted by the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India ( Amendment ) Act, 1947 ( 11 of 1947 ), s. 22 ( w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1947). Earlier it was inserted by the`
  line `M.O. 1937.`
  line `42. Cash reserves of scheduled banks to be kept with the Bank. — 11 [( 1 ) Every bank included in`
  line `the Second Schedule shall maintain with the Bank an average daily balance the amount of which shall not`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1956, s. 4, for section 37 (w.e.f. 6 - 10 - 1956).`
  line `2. The proviso omitted by Act 48 of 1957, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31 - 10 - 1957).`
  line `3. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C”.`
  line `4. The words and figures “to re - issue any rupee coin delivered under section 36 nor” omitted by Act 55 of 1963, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 -`
  line `1964).`
  line `5. The words “and as provided in that section” omitted by Ordinance 4 of 1940, s. 3.`
  line `6. The words “or by delivery to the Central Government under that sections” omitted by Act 55 of 1963, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 1964).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule, for “five” (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 23 of 1947, s. 4, for sections 40 and 41 (w.e.f. 18 - 4 - 1947).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 54 of 1953, s. 5 (w.e.f. 30 - 12 - 1953).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 5, for “Foreign Exchange Regulation Act, 1947 (7 of 1947)” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 1984).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 38 of 1956, s. 5, for sub - section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. (6 - 10 - 1956).`
