obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line 32
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( b ) the total amount of legal tender notes and coins held by it in India,`
  line `( c ) the balance held by it at the Bank in India,`
  line `( d ) the balances held by it at other banks in current account and the money at call and short notice`
  line `in India,`
  line `( e ) the investments (at book value) in Central and State Government securities including treasury`
  line `bi lls and treasury deposit receipts,`
  line `( f ) the amount of advances in India,`
  line `( g ) the inland bills purchased and discounted in India 2 [and foreign bills purchased and`
  line discounted].
  line `3 [at the close of business on each alternate Friday, and every such return shall b e sent not later than seven`
  line `days after the date to which it relates ]:`
  line `4 [Provided that the Bank may, by notification in the Gazette of India, delete or modify or add to any`
  line `of the particulars specified in the foregoing clauses:`
  line `Provided further that] where 5 [such alternate] Friday is a public holiday under the Negotiable`
  line `Instruments Act, 1881 (26 of 1881), for one or more offices of a scheduled bank the return shall give the`
  line `preceding working day ’ s figures in respect of such office or offices, but shall nevertheless be deemed to`
  line `relate to that Friday:`
  line `6 [ Provided also that where the Bank is satisfied that the furnishing of a fortnightly return under this`
  line `sub - section is impracticable in the case of any scheduled bank by reason of the geographical position o f`
  line `the bank and its branche s, the Bank may allow such bank —`
  line `( i ) to furnish a provisional return for the fortnight within the period aforesaid to be followed by a`
  line `final return not later than twenty days after the date to which it relates, or`
  line `( ii ) to furnish in lieu of a fortnightly return a monthly return to be sent not later than twenty days`
  line `after the end of the month to which it relates giving the details specified in this sub - section in respect`
  line `of such bank at the close of business for the month.]]`
  line `5 [( 2A ) Where the last Friday of a month is not an alternate Friday for the purpose of sub - section( 2 ),`
  line `every scheduled bank shall send to the Bank, a special return giving the details specified in sub - section`
  line `( 2 ) as at the close of business on such last Friday or where such last Friday is a public holiday under the`
  line `Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881 (26 of 1881), as at the close of business on the preceding working day`
  line `and such return shall be sent not later than seven days after the date to which it relates.]`
  line `7 [( 3 ) If the average daily balance held at the Bank by a scheduled bank during any 8 [fortnight] is`
  line `below the minimum prescribed by or under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 1A ), such scheduled bank shall`
  line `be liable to pay to the Bank in respect of that 8 [fortnight] penal interest at a rate of three per cent. above`
  line `the bank rate on the amount by which such balance with the Bank falls short of the prescribed minimum,`
  line `and if during the next succeeding 8 [fortnight], such average daily balance is still below t he prescribed`
  line `minimum, the rates of penal interest shall be increased to a rate of five per cent, above the bank rate in`
  line `respect of that 8 [fortnight] and each subsequent 8 [fortnight] during which the default continues on the`
  line `amount by which such balance at the Bank falls short of the prescribed minimum.]`
  line `1. Clause ( aa ) omitted by Act 51 of 1974, s. 11 (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974). Earlier inserted by Act 54 of 1953, s. 6 (w.e.f. 30 - 12 - 1953).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 54 of 1953, s. 6 (w.e.f. 30 - 12 - 1953).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 6, for “at the close of business on each Friday, and every such return shall be sent not later tha n five`
  line `days after the date to which it relates” (w.e.f. 29 - 3 - 1985).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 11, for “Provided that” (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 6 (w.e.f. 29 - 3 - 1985).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for the third proviso (w.e.f. 29 - 3 - 1 985).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 38 of 1956, s. 5, for sub - section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 6 - 10 - 1956).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 6, for “week” (w.e.f. 29 - 3 - 1985).`
