obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line 33
  line `1 [( 3A ) When under the provisions of sub - section ( 3 ) penal interest at the increased rate of five per`
  line `cent, above the bank rate has become payable by a scheduled bank, 2 [if thereafter the average daily`
  line `balan ce held at the Bank during the next succeeding 3 [fortnight] is still below the prescribed minimum, —`
  line `( a ) every director, manager or secretary of the scheduled bank, who is knowingly and wilfully a`
  line `party to the default, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and with a`
  line `further fine which may extend to five hundred rupees for each subsequent 3 [fortnight] during which`
  line `the default continues, and`
  line `( b ) the Bank may prohibit the scheduled bank from receiving after the said 3 [fortnight] any fresh`
  line deposit,]
  line `and, if default is made by the scheduled bank in complying with the prohibition referred to in clause ( b ),`
  line `every director and officer of the scheduled bank who is kn owingly and wilfully a party to such default or`
  line `who through negligence or otherwise contributes to such default shall in respect of each such default be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees and with a further fine which may extend`
  line `t o five hundred rupees for each day after the first on which a deposit received in contravention of such`
  line `prohibition is retained by the scheduled bank.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub - section “ officer ” includes a 4 *** manager, secretary, branch manager, and`
  line `branch secretary.]`
  line `( 4 ) Any scheduled bank failing to comply with the provisions of sub - section ( 2 ) 5 [shall be liable to`
  line `pay to the Bank] a penalty of one hundred rupees for each day during which the failure continues.`
  line `6 [( 5 ) ( a ) The penalties imposed by sub - secti ons ( 3 ) and ( 4 ) shall be payable within a period of`
  line `fourteen days from the date on which a notice issued by the Bank demanding the payment of the same is`
  line `served on the scheduled bank, and in the event of failure of the scheduled bank to pay the same within`
  line `such period, may be levied by a direction of the principal civil court having jurisdiction in the area where`
  line `an office of the defaulting bank is situated, such direction to be mode only upon an application made in`
  line `this behalf to the court by the Bank;`
  line `( b ) when the court makes a direction under clause ( a ), it shall issue a certificate specifying the sum`
  line `payable by the scheduled bank and every such certificate shall be enforceable in the same manner as if it`
  line `were a decree made by the court in a suit;`
  line `( c ) not withstanding anything contained in this section, if the Bank is satisfied that the defaulting bank`
  line `and sufficient cause for its failure to comply with the provisions of sub - section ( 1 ), ( 1A ) or ( 2 ), it may not`
  line `demand the payment of the penal interest of the penalty, as the case may be.]`
  line `7 [( 6 ) The Bank shall, save as hereinafter provided, by notifi cation in the Gazette of India, —`
  line `( a ) direct the inclusion in the Second Schedule of any bank not already so included which carries`
  line `on the business of banking 8 [i n India] and which —`
  line `( i ) has a paid - up capital and reserve of an aggregate value of not less than five lakhs or`
  line `rupees, and`
  line `( ii ) satisfies and Bank that its affairs are not being conducted in a manner detrimental to the`
  line `interests of its depositors, and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 1940, s. 2 (w.e.f. 27 - 22 - 1940).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 38 of 1956, s. 5, for certain words (w.e.f. 6 - 10 - 1956).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 6, for “week” (w.e.f. 29 - 3 - 1985).`
  line `4. The words “managing agent” omitted by Act 32 of 1951, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for “shall be liable to pay to the Central Government or to the Bank, as the case may be, or to each,”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 35 of 1962, s. 4, for sub - section ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 15 - 9 - 1962).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 10 of 1949, s. 55 and the First Schedule, for sub - section ( 6 ) (w.e.f. 16 - 3 - 1949).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 16, for “in any State of India” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
