  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  sourcePage 34
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line 34
  line `( iii ) 1 [is a State co - operative bank or a company] as defined 2 [section 3of the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956), or an institution notified by the Central Government in this behalf] or a`
  line `corporation or a company incorporated by or under any law in force in any place 3 [outside India];`
  line `( b ) direct the exclusion from that Schedule of any scheduled bank, —`
  line `( i ) the aggregate value of whose paid - up capital and reserves becomes at any time less than`
  line `five lakhs of rupees, or`
  line `( ii ) which is, in the opinion of the Bank after making an inspection under section 35 of the`
  line `4 [ Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) ], conducting its affairs to the detriment of the`
  line `interests of its depositors, or`
  line `( iii ) which goes into liquidation or othe rwise ceases to carry on banking business:`
  line `Provided that the Bank may, on application of the scheduled bank concerned and subject to`
  line `such conditions, if any, as it may impose, defer the making of a direction under sub - clause ( i ) or`
  line `sub - clause ( ii ) of claus e ( b ) for such period as the Bank consider reasonable to give the scheduled`
  line `bank an opportunity of increasing the aggregate value of its paid - up capital and reserves to not`
  line `less than five lakhs of rupees or, as the case may be, of removing the defects in t he conduct of its`
  line affairs;
  line `( c ) alter the description in that Schedule whenever any scheduled bank changes its name.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub - section the expression “ value ” means the real or exchangeable value and`
  line `not the nominal value which may be shown in the boo k s of the bank concerned; and if any dispute arises`
  line `in computing the aggregate value of the paid - up capital and reserves of a bank, a determination thereof by`
  line `the Bank shall be final for the purposes of this sub - section.]`
  line `5 [( 6A ) In considering whether a State co - operative bank or a regional rural bank should be included in`
  line `or excluded from the Second Schedule, it shall be competent for the Bank to act on a certificate from the`
  line `National Bank on the question whether or not a State co - operative ban k or a regional rural bank, as the`
  line `case may be, satisfies the requirements as to paid - up capital and reserves or whether its affairs are not`
  line `being conducted in a manner detrimental to the interests of its depositors.]`
  line `6 [( 7 ) The Bank may, for such period an d subject to such conditions as may be specified, grant to any`
  line `scheduled bank such exemptions from the provisions of this section as it thinks fit with reference to all or`
  line `any of its offices or with reference to the whole or any part of its assets and liab ilities.]`
  line `7 [ 43. Publication of consolidated statement by the Bank. — The Bank shall cause to be published`
  line `each 8 [fortnight] a consolidated statement showing the aggregate liabilities and assets of all the scheduled`
  line `banks together, based on the returns and in formation received under this Act or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force.]`
  line `9 [ 43A. Protection of action taken in good faith. — ( 1 ) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the Bank or any of its officers for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in`
  line `pursuance of section 42 or section 43 10 [or in pursuance of the provisions of Chapter IIIA].`
  line `( 2 ) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Bank or any of its officers for any damage`
  line `caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance`
  line `of section 42 or section 43 10 [or in pursuance of the provisions of Chapter IIIA].]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1965, s. 6, for “is a company” (w.e.f. 1 - 3 - 1966).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 1957, s. 4, for “clause ( 2 ) of section 2 of the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913)” (w.e.f. 8 - 6 - 1957).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 16, for “outside the States of India” (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 3, for “Banking Companies Act, 1949” (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 61 of 1981, s. 61 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 12 - 7 - 1982).`
  line `6. I ns. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 12, for section 43 (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 6, for “week” (w.e.f. 29 - 3 - 1985).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 54 of 1953, s. 7 (w.e.f. 30 - 12 - 1953).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 35 of 1962, s. 5 (w.e.f. 15 - 9 - 1962).`
