  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  sourcePage 35
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line 35
  line `44. [ Power to require returns from co - operative banks ]. — [ Omitted by the Banking Laws`
  line `( Application to Co - operative Societies ) Act, 1965 (23 of 1965), s. 7 ( w.e.f. 1 - 3 - 1966).]`
  line `1 [ 45. Appointment of agents. — ( 1 ) Unless otherwise directed by the Central Government with`
  line `reference to any place, the Bank may, having regard to public interest, convenience of banking, banking`
  line `development and such other factors which in its opinion are relevant in this regard, appoint the National`
  line `Bank, or the State Bank, or a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking`
  line `Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), or a corresponding new`
  line `bank constituted under section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings)`
  line `Act, 1980 (40 of 1980), or any subsidiary bank as defined in the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks)`
  line `Act, 1959 (38 of 1959), as its agent at all places, or at any place in India for such purposes as the Bank`
  line `may specify.`
  line `( 2 ) When any bank is appointed by the Bank as its agent under sub - section ( 1 ) to receive on behalf of`
  line `the Bank any payment required to be made into the Bank, or any bill, hundies or other securities required`
  line `to be delivered into the Bank, under any law or rule, regulations or other instructions having the force of`
  line `law, the same may be paid or delivered into the ba nk so appointed as the agent of the Bank.]`
  line `2 [ CHAPTER IIIA`
  line `C OLLECTION AND FURNISHING OF CREDIT INFORMATION`
  line `45A. Definitions. — In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ banking company ” means a banking company as defined in section 5 of the 3 [Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) ] and includes the State Bank of India, 4 [any subsidiary bank as`
  line `defined in the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959), any correspond ing new`
  line `bank constituted by section 3 of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings)`
  line `Act, 1970 (5 of 1970), and any other financial institution notified by the Central Government in this`
  line behalf];
  line `( b ) “ borrower ” means any person to whom any credit limit has been sanctioned by any banking`
  line `company, whether availed of or not, and includes —`
  line `( i ) in the case of a company or corporation, its subsidiaries;`
  line `( ii ) in the case of a Hindu undivided family, any member thereof or any firm in which such`
  line `member is a partner;`
  line `( iii ) in the case of a firm, any partner thereof or any other firm in which such partner is a`
  line `partner; and`
  line `( iv ) in the case of an individual, any firm in which such individual is a partner;`
  line `( c ) “ credit information ” me ans any information relating to —`
  line `( i ) the amounts and the nature of loans or advances and other credit facilities granted by a`
  line `banking company to any borrower or class of borrowers;`
  line `( ii ) the nature of security taken from any borrower 5 [or class of borrowers] for credit facilities`
  line `6 [granted to him or to such class; ]`
  line `( iii ) the guarantee furnished by a banking company for any of its customers 5 [or any class of`
  line `its customers];`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 61 of 1981, s. 61 and the Second Schedule, for section 45 (w.e.f. 12 - 7 - 1982).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 35 of 1962, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1 - 9 - 1962).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 3, for “Banking Companies Act, 1949” (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for “or any other banking or financial institution notified by the Central Government in this behalf” (w.e.f.`
  line `13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 13, ibid., (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for “granted to him; a nd” (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
