obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line 36
  line `1 [( iv ) the means, antecedents, history of financial transactions and the creditworthiness of any`
  line `borrower or class of borrowers;`
  line `( v ) any other information which the Bank may consider to be relevant for the more orderly`
  line `regulation of credit or credit policy.]`
  line `45B. Power of Bank to collect credit information. — The Bank may —`
  line `( a ) collect, in such manner as it may think fit, credit information from banking companies; and`
  line `( b ) furnish such information to any banking company in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `section 45D.`
  line `45C. Power to call for returns containing credit information. — ( 1 ) For the purpo se of enabling the`
  line `Bank to discharge its functions under this Chapter, it may at any time direct any banking company to`
  line `submit to it such statements relating to such credit information and in such form and within such time as`
  line `may be specified by the Bank f rom time to time.`
  line `( 2 ) A banking company shall, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any law for the`
  line `time being in force on in any instrument regulating the constitution thereof or in any agreement executed`
  line `by it, relating to the secrecy of its dealings with its constituents, be bound to comply with any direction`
  line `issued under sub - section ( 1 ).`
  line `45D. Procedure for furnishing credit information to banking companies. — ( 1 ) A banking`
  line `company may, in connection with any financial arrangement entered into or proposed to be entered into`
  line `by it, with any person, make an application to the Bank in such form as the Bank may specify requesting`
  line `it to furnish the applicant with such credit information as may be specified in the application.`
  line `( 2 ) On receipt of an application under sub - section ( 1 ), the Bank shall, as soon as may be, furnish the`
  line `applicant with such credit information relating to the matters specified in the application, as may be in its`
  line `possession:`
  line `Provided that the information so furnished shall not disclose the names of the banking companies`
  line `which have submitted such information to the Bank.`
  line `( 3 ) The Bank may in respect of each application levy such fees, not exceeding twenty - five rupees, as`
  line `it may deem fit for furnishing credit information.`
  line `45E. Disclosure of information prohibited. — ( 1 ) Any credit information contained in any statement`
  line `submitted by a banking company under section 45C or furnished by the Bank to any banking company`
  line `under section 45D, shall be treated as confidential and shall not, except for the purposes of this Chapter,`
  line `be published or otherwise disclosed.`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing in this section shall apply to —`
  line `( a ) the disclosure by any banking company, with the previous permission of the Bank, of any`
  line `information furnished to the Bank under se ction 45C;`
  line `( b ) the publication by the Bank, if it considers necessary in the public interest so to do, of any`
  line `information collected by it under section 45C, in such consolidated form as it may think fit without`
  line `disclosing the name of any banking company or its borrowers;`
  line `2 [( c ) the disclosure or publication by the banking company or by the Bank of any credit`
  line `information to any other banking company or in accordance with the practice and usage c u stomary`
  line `among bankers or as permitted or required under any other law;`
  line `3 [ ( d ) the disclosures of any credit information under the Credit Information Com panies`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 2005 (30 of 2005): ]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 13 (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 30 of 2005, s. 34 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 14 - 12 - 2006).`
