obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line 38
  line `( c ) any financial institution specified in or under section 6A of the Industrial`
  line `Development Bank of India Act, 1964 (18 of 1964), or`
  line `( d ) any other institution that may be specified by the Bank in this behalf;`
  line `( v ) amounts received in the ordinar y course of business, by way of —`
  line `( a ) security deposit,`
  line `( b ) dealership d eposit,`
  line `( c ) earnest money, or`
  line `( d ) advance against orders for goods, properties or services;`
  line `( vi ) any amount received from an individual or a firm or an association of individuals not`
  line `being a body corporate, registered under any enactment relating to money lending which is for`
  line `the time being in force in any State; and`
  line `( vii ) any amount received by way of subscriptions in respect of a chit.`
  line `Explanation I. — “ Chit ” has the meaning assigned to it in clause ( b ) of section 2 of the Chit Funds Act,`
  line `1982 (40 of 1982).`
  line `Explanation II. — Any credit given by a seller to a buyer on the sale of any property (whether movable`
  line `or immovable) shall not be deemed to be deposit for the purposes of this clause;]`
  line `1 [ Explanation III. — The amounts accepted by a co - operative society from the members or`
  line `shareholders, by whatever name called, but excluding the amounts received as share capital, shall be`
  line `deemed to be deposits for the purposes of this clause, if such members or shareholders are nominal or`
  line `associate members, by whatever name c alled, who do not have full voting rights in the meetings of such`
  line `co - operative society.]`
  line `2 [( c ) “ financial institution ” means any non - banking institution which carries on as its business or`
  line `part of its business any of th e following activities, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the financing, whether by way of making loans or advances or otherwise, of any activity`
  line `other than its own;`
  line `( ii ) the acquisition of shares, stock, bonds, debentures or securities issued by a Government`
  line `or local authority or other marketable securities of a like nature;`
  line `( iii ) letting or delivering of any goods to a hirer under a hire - purchase agreement as defined`
  line `in clause ( c ) of section 2 of the Hire - Purchase Act, 1972 (26 of 1972);`
  line `( iv ) the carrying on of any class of insurance business;`
  line `( v ) managing, conducting or supervising, as foreman, agent or in any other capacity, of chits`
  line `or kuries as defined in any law which is for the time being in force in any State, or any business,`
  line `which is similar thereto;`
  line `( vi ) collecting, for any purpose or un der any scheme or arrangement by whatever name`
  line `called, monies in lump sum or otherwise, by way of subscriptions or by sale of units, or other`
  line `instruments or in any other manner and awarding prizes or gifts, whether in cash or king, or`
  line `disbursing monies in any other way, to persons from whom monies are collected or to any other`
  line person,
  line `3 [but does not include any institution, which carrie s on as its principal business, —`
  line `( a ) agricultural operations; or`
  line `( aa ) industrial activity; or]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2019, s. 4 2 the second schedule (w.e.f. 21 - 2 - 2019).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 17, for clause ( c ) (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 23 of 1997, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 9 - 1 - 1997).`
