obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line 39
  line `( b ) the purchase, or sale o f any goods (other than securities) or the providing of any services; or`
  line `( c ) the purchase, construction or sale of immovable property, so, however, that no portion of the`
  line `income of the institution is derived from the financing of purchases, constructions o r sales of immovable`
  line `property by other persons;]`
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, “industrial activity” means any activity specified`
  line `in sub - clauses ( i ) to ( xviii ) of clause ( c ) of section 2 of the Industrial Development Bank of India Act,`
  line `19 64 (18 of 1964);]`
  line `( d ) “ firm ” means a firm as defined in the Indian Partnership Act, 1932 (9 of 1932) 2 ***;`
  line `( e ) “ non - banking institution ” means a company, corporation 3 [or co - operative society];`
  line `1 [( f ) “ non - b anking financial company” means —`
  line `( i ) a financial institution which is a company;`
  line `( ii ) a non - banking institution which is a company and which has as its principal business the`
  line `receiving of deposits, under any scheme or arrangement or in any other manner, or lending in any`
  line manner;
  line `( iii ) such other non - banking institution or class of such institutions, as the Bank may, with the`
  line `previous approval of the Central Government and by notification in the Official Gazette, specify.]`
  line `4 [ 45 - IA. Requirement of registration and net owned fund. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Chapter or in any other law for the time being in force, no non - banking financial`
  line `company shall commence or carry on the business of a non - banking financial institution without —`
  line `( a ) obtaining a certificate of registration issued under this Chapter; and`
  line `5 [( b ) having the net owned fund of twenty - five lakh rupees or such other amount, not exceeding`
  line `hundred crore rupees, as the Bank may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify:`
  line `Provided that the Bank may notify different amo unts of net owned fund for different categories of`
  line `non - banking financial companies.]`
  line `( 2 ) Every non - banking financial company shall make an application for registration to the Bank in`
  line `such form as the Bank may specify:`
  line `Provided that a non - banking financial company in existence on the commencement of the Reserve`
  line `Bank of India (Amendment) Act, 1997 (23 of 1997) shall make an application for registration to the Bank`
  line `before the expiry of six months from such commencement and notwithstanding anything contained i n`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) may continue to carry on the business of a non - banking financial institution until a`
  line `certificate of registration is issued to it or rejection of application for registration is communicated to it.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), a non - banking financial company in`
  line `existence on the commencement of the Reserve Bank of India (Amendment) Act, 1997 (23 of 1997) and`
  line `having a net owned fund of less than twenty - five lakh rupees may, for the purpose of enabling such`
  line `compan y to fulfil the requirement of the net owned fund, continue to carry on the business of a no n -`
  line `banking financial institution —`
  line `( i ) for a period of there years from such commencement; or`
  line `( ii ) for such further period as the Bank may, after recording the reasons in writing for so doing,`
  line extend,
  line `subject to the condition that such company shall, within three months of fulfilling the requirement of the`
  line `net owned fund, inform the Bank about such fulfillment:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 1997, s. 2 (w.e.f. 9 - 1 - 1997).`
  line `2. The words “, of which the capital subscribed by its partners exceeds one lakh of r upees” omitted by Act 1 of 1984, s. 9`
  line `(w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 1984).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for “, co - operative society or firm” (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 1984).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 1997, s. 3 (w.e.f. 9 - 1 - 1997).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 137, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 9 - 8 - 2019)`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-40
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Page 40`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  sourcePage 40
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line 40
  line `Provided that the period allowed to continue busines s under this sub - section shall in no case exceed`
  line `six years in the aggregate.`
  line `( 4 ) The Bank, for the purpose of considering the application for registration, may require to be`
  line `satisfied by an inspection of the books of the non - banking financial company or ot herwise that the`
  line `foll owing conditions are fulfilled: —`
  line `( a ) that the non - banking financial company is or shall be in a position to pay its present or future`
  line `depositors in full as and when their claims accrue;`
  line `( b ) that the affairs of the non - banking financial company are not being or are not likely to be`
  line `conducted in a manner detrimental to the interest of its present or future depositors;`
  line `( c ) that the general character of the management or the proposed management of the non - banking`
  line `financial company shall not be prejudicial to the public interest or the interests of its depositors;`
  line `( d ) that the non - banking financial company has adequate capital structure and earning prospects;`
  line `( e ) that the public interest shall be served by the grant of certificate of registra tion to the non -`
  line `banking financial company to commence or to carry on the business of India;`
  line `( f ) that the grant of certificate of registration shall not be prejudicial to the operation and`
  line `consolidation of the financial sector consistent with monetary stabi lity, and economic growth`
  line `considering such other relevant factors which the Bank may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify; and`
  line `( g ) any other condition, fulfilment of which in the opinion of the Bank, shall be necessary to`
  line `ensure that the comme ncement of or carrying on of the business in India by a non - banking financial`
  line `company shall not be prejudicial to the public interest or in the interests of the depositors.`
  line `( 5 ) The Bank may, after being satisfied that the conditions specified in subsection ( 4 ) are fulfilled,`
  line `grant a certificate of registration subject to such conditions which it may consider fit to impose.`
  line `( 6 ) The Bank cancel a certificate of registration granted to a non - banking financial company und er`
  line `this section if such company —`
  line `( i ) cea ses to carry on the business of a non - banking financial institution in India; or`
  line `( ii ) has failed to comply with any condition subject to which the certificate of registration had`
  line `been issued to it; or`
  line `( iii ) at any time fails to fulfil any of the conditions referred to in clauses ( d ) to ( g ) of sub - section`
  line `( 4 ); or`
  line `( iv ) fails —`
  line `( a ) to comply with any direction issued by the Bank under the provisions of this Chapter; or`
  line `( b ) to maintain accounts in accordance with the requirements of any law or any direction or`
  line `order issued by the Bank under the provisions of this Chapter; or`
  line `( c ) to submit or offer for inspection its books of account and other relevant documents when`
  line `so demanded by an inspecting authority of the Bank; or`
  line `( v ) has been prohibited from accepting dep osit by an order made by the Bank under the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter and such order has been in force for a period of not less than three months:`
  line `Provided that before cancelling a certificate of registration on the ground that the non - banking`
  line `financial c ompany has failed to company with the provisions of clause ( ii ) or has failed to fulfil any`
  line `of the conditions referred to in clause ( iii ) the Bank, unless it is of the opinion that the delay in`
  line `cancelling the certificate of registration shall be prejudicia l to public interest or the interest of the`
  line `depositors or the non - banking financial company, shall give an opportunity to such company on such`
  line `term as the Bank may specify for taking necessary steps to comply with such provision or fulfilment`
  line `of such condi tion:`
  line `Provided further that before making any order of cancellation of certificate of registration, such`
  line `company shall be given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-41
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Page 41`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  sourcePage 41
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line 41
  line `( 7 ) A company aggrieved by the order of rejection of application for registration or ca ncellation of`
  line `certificate of registration may prefer an Appeal, within a period of thirty days from the date on which`
  line `such order of rejection or cancellation is communicated to it, to the Central Government and the decision`
  line `of the Central Government where an appeal has been preferred to it, or of the Bank where no appeal has`
  line `been preferred, shall be final:`
  line `Provided that before making any order of rejection of appeal, such company shall be given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `Explanations. — Fo r the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( I ) “ net owned fund ” means —`
  line `( a ) the aggregate of the paid - up equity capital and free reserves as disclosed in the latest`
  line `balance - sheet of the com pany after deducting there from —`
  line `( i ) accumulated balance of loss;`
  line `( ii ) deferred reve nue expenditure; and`
  line `( iii ) other intangible assets; and`
  line `( b ) further redu ced by the amounts representing —`
  line `( 1 ) investments of such company in shares of —`
  line `( i ) its subsidiaries;`
  line `( ii ) companies in the same group;`
  line `( iii ) all other non - banking financial companies; and`
  line `( 2 ) the book value of debentures, bonds, outstanding loans and advances (including hire -`
  line `purchase and lease finan ce) made to, and deposits with, —`
  line `( i ) subsidiaries of such company; and`
  line `( ii ) companies in the same group,`
  line `to the extent such book value exceeds ten per cent. of ( a ) above.`
  line `( II ) “ subsidiaries ” and “ companies in the same group ” shall have the same meanings assigned to`
  line `them in the Companies Act, 1956, (1 of 1956).]`
  line `45 - IB. Maintenance of percentage of assets. — ( 1 ) Every non - banking financial company shall`
  line `invest and continue to invest in India in unencumbered approved securities, valued at a price not`
  line `exceeding the current market price of such securities, an amount which, at the close of business on any`
  line `day, shall not be less than five per cen t. or such higher percentage not exceeding twenty - five per cent. as`
  line `the Bank may, from time to time and by notification in the Official Gazette, specify, of the deposits`
  line `outstanding at the close of business on the last working day of the second preceding q uarter:`
  line `Provided that the Bank may specify different percentages of investment in respect of different classes`
  line `of non - banking financial companies.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purpose of ensuring compliance with the provisions of this section, the Bank may require`
  line `every no n - banking financial company to furnish a return to it in such form, in such manner and for such`
  line `period as may be specified by the Bank.`
  line `( 3 ) If the amount invested by a non - banking financial company at the close of business on any day`
  line `falls below the rate s pecified under sub - section ( 1 ), such company shall be liable to pay to the Bank, in`
  line `respect of such shortfall, a penal interest at a rate of three per cent. per annum above the bank rate on such`
  line `amount by which the amount actually invested falls short of th e specified percentage, and where the`
  line `shortfall continues in the subsequent quarters, the rate of penal interest shall be five per cent. per annum`
  line `above the bank rate on such shortfall for each subsequent quarter.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-42
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Page 42`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  sourcePage 42
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line 42
  line `( 4 ) ( a ) The penal interest payable under su b - section ( 3 ) shall be payable within a period of fourteen`
  line `days from the date on which a notice issued by the Bank demanding payment of the same is served on the`
  line `non - banking financial company and, in the event of a failure of the non - banking financial comp any to pay`
  line `the same within such period, penalty may be levied by a direction of the principal civil court having`
  line `jurisdiction in the area where an office of the defaulting non - banking financial company is situated and`
  line `such direction shall be made only upon an application made in this behalf to the court by the Bank; and`
  line `( b ) when the court makes a direction under clause ( a ), it shall issue a certificate specifying the sum`
  line `payable by the non - banking financial company and every such certificate shall be enforceable in the same`
  line `manner as if it were a decree made by the court in a suit.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, if the Bank is satisfied that the defaulting non -`
  line `banking financial company had sufficient cause for its failure to co mply with the provisions of sub -`
  line `section ( 1 ), it may not demand the payment of the penal interest.`
  line `Explanation. — F or the purpose of this section, —`
  line `( i ) “ approved securities ” means securities of any State Government or of the Central Government`
  line `and such bonds, both the principal whereof and the interest whereon shall have been fully and`
  line `unconditionally guaranteed by any such Government;`
  line `( ii ) “ unencumbered approved securities ” includes the approved securities lodged by the non -`
  line `banking financial company with another institution for an advance or any other arrangement to the`
  line `extent to which such securities have not been drawn against or availed of or encumbered in any`
  line manner;
  line `( ii i ) “ quarter ” means the period of three months ending on the last day of Marc h, June, September`
  line `or December.`
  line `45 - IC. Reserve fund. — ( 1 ) Every non - banking financial company shall create a reserve fund the`
  line `transfer therein a sum not less than twenty per cent. of its net profit every year as disclosed in the profit`
  line `and loss account and before any dividend is declared.`
  line `( 2 ) No appropriation of any sum from the reserve fund shall be made by the non - banking financial`
  line `company except for the purpose as may be specified by the Bank from time to time and every such`
  line `appropriation shall be reported to the Bank within twenty - one days from the date of such withdrawal:`
  line `Provided that the Bank may, in any particular case and for sufficient cause being shown, extend the`
  line `period of twenty - one days by such further period as it thinks fit or condone any delay in making such`
  line report.
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), the Central Government may, on the`
  line `recommendation of the Bank and having regard to the adequacy o f the paid - up capital and reserves of a`
  line `non - banking financial company in relation to its deposit liabilities, declare by order in writing that the`
  line `provisions of sub - section ( 1 ) shall not be applicable to the non - banking financial company for such period`
  line `as may be specified in the order:`
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made unless the amount in the reserve fund under sub - section ( 1 )`
  line `together with the amount in the share premium account is not less than the paid - up capital of the non -`
  line `banking financial co mpany.]`
  line `1 [ 45 - ID. Power of Bank to remove directors from office. — ( 1 ) Where the Bank is satisfied that in`
  line `the public interest or to prevent the affairs of a non - banking financial company being conducted in a`
  line `manner detrimental to the interest of the depositors or creditors, or financial stability or for securing the`
  line `proper management of such company, it is necessary so to do, the Bank may, by order and for reasons to`
  line `be recorded in writing, remove from office, a director (by whatever name called) of s uch company, other`
  line `than Government owned non - banking financial company with effect from such date as may be specified`
  line `in the said order.`
  line `( 2 ) No order under sub - section ( 1 ) shall be made unless the director concerned has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of making a representation to the Bank against the proposed order:`
  line `1. Ins. by 23 of 2019, s. 138 (w.e.f. 9 - 8 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-43
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Page 43`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  sourcePage 43
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line 43
  line `Provided that if, in the opinion of the Bank, any delay will be detrimental to the interest of the said`
  line `company or its depositors, the Bank may, at the time of giving the aforesaid opportun ity or at any time`
  line `thereafter, by order direct that, pending the consideration of the representation, if any, the director, shall`
  line `not, with effect from the date of such order`
  line `( a ) act as such director of that company;`
  line `( b ) in any way, whether directly or indirectly, be concerned with or take part in the management of`
  line `that company.`
  line `( 3 ) Where any order is made in respect of a director of a company under sub - section ( 1 ), he shall cease`
  line `to be a director of that non - banking financial company and shall not, in a ny way, whether directly or`
  line `indirectly, be concerned with, or take part in the management of any non - banking financial company for`
  line `such period not exceeding five years at a time as may be specified in the order.`
  line `( 4 ) Where an order under sub - section ( 1 ) has been made, the Bank may, by order in writing, appoint a`
  line `suitable person in place of the director, who has been so removed from his office, with effect from such`
  line `date as may be specified in such order.`
  line `( 5 ) Any person appointed under sub - section ( 4 ) shall, —`
  line `( a ) hold office during the pleasure of the Bank and subject thereto for a period not exceeding three`
  line `years or such further periods not exceeding three years at a time;`
  line `( b ) not incur any obligation or liability by reason only of his being a director for anything done or`
  line `omitted to be done in good faith in the execution of the duties of his office or in relation thereto.`
  line `( 6 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any contract,`
  line `memorandum or articles of associa tion, on the removal of a director from office under this section, such`
  line `director shall not be entitled to claim any compensation for the loss or termination from office.`
  line `45 - IE. Supersession of Board of directors of non - banking financial company (other than`
  line `Government Company). — ( 1 ) Where the Bank is satisfied that in the public interest or to prevent the`
  line `affairs of a non - banking financial company being conducted in a manner detrimental to the interest of the`
  line `depositors or creditors, or of the non - banking fin ancial company (other than Government Company), or`
  line `for securing the proper management of such company or for financial stability, it is necessary so to do,`
  line `the Bank may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, by order, supersede the Board of Directors of s uch`
  line `company for a period not exceeding five years as may be specified in the order, which may be extended`
  line `from time to time, so, however, that the total period shall not exceed five years.`
  line `( 2 ) The Bank may, on supersession of the Board of Directors of the non - banking financial company`
  line `under sub - section ( 1 ), appoint a suitable person as the Administrator for such period as it may determine.`
  line `( 3 ) The Bank may issue such directions to the Administrator as it may deem appropriate and the`
  line `Administrator shall be b ound to follow such directions.`
  line `( 4 ) Upon making the order of supersession of the Board of Directors of a non - banking financial`
  line `company, —`
  line `( a ) the chairman, managing director and other directors shall from the date of super session of the`
  line `Board of Directors vacate their offices;`
  line `( b ) all the powers, functions and duties, which may, by or under the provisions of this Act or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, be exercised and discharged by or on behalf of the Board of`
  line `Directors of such non - banking finan cial company or by a resolution passed in general meeting of such`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-44
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Page 44`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  sourcePage 44
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line 44
  line `non - banking financial company, shall, until the Board of Directors of such company is reconstituted,`
  line `be exercised and discharged by the Administrator referred to in sub - section ( 2 ).`
  line `( 5 ) ( a ) The Bank may constitute a committee consisting of three or more members who have`
  line `experience in law, finance, banking, administration or accountancy to assist the Administrator in`
  line `discharge of his duties.`
  line `( b ) The committee shall meet at such times and plac es and observe such rules of procedure as may`
  line `be specified by the Bank.`
  line `( 6 ) The salary and allowances payable to the Administrator and the members of the committee`
  line `constituted by the Bank shall be such as may be specified by the Bank and be paid by the concerned non -`
  line `banking financial company.`
  line `( 7 ) On or before the expiration of the period of super session of the Board of Directors as specified in`
  line `the order issued under sub - section ( 1 ), the Administrator of the non - banking financial company shall`
  line `facilitat e reconstitution of the Board of Directors of the non - banking financial company.`
  line `( 8 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any contract,`
  line `no person shall be entitled to claim any compensation for the loss or t ermination of his office.`
  line `( 9 ) The Administrator referred to in sub - section ( 2 ) shall vacate office immediately after the Board of`
  line `Directors of the non - banking financial company has been reconstituted.]`
  line `45J. Bank to regulate or prohibit issue of prospectus or advertisement soliciting deposits of`
  line `money. — The Bank may, if it consider necessary in the public interest so to do, by general or special`
  line `order, —`
  line `( a ) regulate or prohibit the issue by any non - banking institution of any prospectus or`
  line `advertisement soliciting deposits of money from the public, and`
  line `( b ) specify the conditions subject to which any such prospectus or advertisement, if not`
  line `prohibited, may be issued.`
  line `1 [ 45JA. Power of Bank to determine policy and issue directions. — ( 1 ) If the Bank is satisfied that,`
  line `in the public interest or to regulate the financial system of the country to its advantage or to prevent the`
  line `affairs of any non - banking financial company being conducted in manner detrimental to the interest of the`
  line `depositors or in a manner prejudicial to the interest of the non - banking financial company, it is necessary`
  line `or expedient so to do, it may determine the policy and give directions to all or any of the non - banking`
  line `financial companies relating to income recognition, accounting standa rds, making of proper provision for`
  line `bad and doubtful debts, capital adequacy based on risk weights for assets and credit conversion factors for`
  line `off balance - sheet items and also relating to deployment of funds by a non - banking financial company or a`
  line `class o f non - banking financial companies or non - banking financial companies generally, as the case may`
  line `be, and such non - banking financial companies shall be bound to follow the policy so determined and the`
  line `direction so issued.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the general ity of the powers vested under sub - section ( 1 ), the Bank may give`
  line `directions to non - banking financial companies generally or to a class of non banking financial companies`
  line `or to any non - banking financial company in particular as to —`
  line `( a ) the purpose for whic h advances or other fund based or non - fund based accommodation may`
  line `not be made; and`
  line `( b ) the maximum amount of advances of other financial accommodation or investment in shares`
  line `and other securities which, having regard to the paid - up capital, reserves and d eposits of the non -`
  line `banking financial company and other relevant considerations, may be made by that non - banking`
  line `financial company to any person or a company or to a group of companies.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 1997, s. 4 (w.e.f. 9 - 1 - 1997).`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-45
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Page 45`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  sourcePage 45
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line 45
  line `45K. Power of Bank to collect information from non - banking institutions as to deposits and to`
  line `give directions. — ( 1 ) The Bank may at any time direct that every non - banking institution shall furnish to`
  line `the Bank, in such form, at such intervals and within such tim e, such statements information or particulars`
  line `relating to or connected with deposits received by the non - banking institution, as may be specified by the`
  line `Bank by general or special order.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the power vested in the Ba nk under sub - section ( 1 ), the`
  line `statements, information or particulars to be furnished under sub - section ( 1 ), may relate to all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely, the amount of the deposits, the purposes and periods for which, and the rates`
  line `of interest and other terms and conditions on which, they are received.`
  line `( 3 ) The Bank may, if it considers necessary in the public interest so to do, give directions to non -`
  line `banking institutions either generally or to any non - banking institution or group of non - banking`
  line `institutions in particular, in respect of any matters relating to or connected with the receipt of deposits,`
  line `including the rates of interest payable on such deposits, and the periods for which deposits may be`
  line received.
  line `( 4 ) If any non - banking institution f ails to comply with any direction given by the Bank under sub -`
  line `section ( 3 ), the Bank may prohibit the acceptance of deposits by that non - banking institution.`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( 6 ) Every non - banking institution receiving deposits shall, if so required by th e Bank and within such`
  line `time as the Bank may specify, cause to be sent at the cost of the non - banking institution a copy of its`
  line `annual balance - sheet arid profit and loss account or other annual accounts to every person from whom the`
  line `non - banking institution holds, as on the last day of the year to which the accounts relate, deposits higher`
  line `than such sum as may be specified by the Bank.`
  line `45L. Power of Bank to call for information from financial institutions and to give directions. —`
  line `( 1 ) If the Bank is satisfied f or the purpose of enabling it to regulate the credit system of the country to its`
  line `advantage it is necessary so to do, it may —`
  line `( a ) require financial institutions either generally or any group of financial institutions or financial`
  line `institution in particular, to furnish to the Bank in such form, at such intervals and within such time,`
  line `such statements, information or particulars relating to the business of such financial institutions or`
  line `institution, as may be specified by the Bank by general or special order;`
  line `( b ) give to such institutions either generally or to any such institution in particular, directions`
  line `relating to the conduct of business by them or by it as financial institutions or institution.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the power vested in the Bank under clause ( a ) of sub -`
  line `section ( 1 ), the statements, information or particulars to be furnished by a financial institution may relate`
  line `to all or any of the following matters, namely, the paid - up capital, reserves or other liabilities, the`
  line `investme nts whether in Government securities or otherwise, the persons to whom, and the purposes and`
  line `periods for which, finance is provided and the terms and conditions, including the rates of interest, on`
  line `which it is provided.`
  line `( 3 ) In issuing directions to any fin ancial institution under clause ( b ) of subsection ( 1 ), the Bank shall`
  line `have due regard to the conditions in which, and the objects for which, the institution has been established,`
  line `its statutory responsibilities, if any, and the effect the business of such f inancial institution is likely to`
  line `have on trends in the money and capital markets.`
  line `45M. Duty of non - banking institutions to furnish statements, etc., required by Bank. — It shall be`
  line `the duty or every non - banking institution to furnish the statements, information or particulars called for,`
  line `and to comply with any direction given to it, under the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line `1. Sub - section ( 5 ) omitted by Act 51 of 1974, s. 18 (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-46
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Page 46`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  sourcePage 46
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line 46
  line `1 [ 45MA. Powers and duties of auditors. — ( 1 ) It shall be the duty of an auditor of a non - banking`
  line `institution to inquire whether or not the non - banking institution has furnished to the Bank such`
  line `statements, information or particulars relating to or connected with deposits received by it, as are required`
  line `to be furnished under this Chapter, and the auditor shall, except where he is satisfied on such inquiry that`
  line `the non - banking institution has furnished such statements, information or particulars, make a report to the`
  line `Bank giving the aggregate amount of such dep osits held by the non - banking institution.`
  line `2 [( 1A ) The Bank may, on being satisfied that it is necessary so to do, in the public interest or in the`
  line `interest of the depositors or for the purpose of proper assessment of the books of accounts, issue`
  line `directions to any non - banking financial company or any class of non - banking financial companies or non -`
  line `banking financial companies generally or to the auditors of such non - banking financial company or`
  line `companies relating to balance - sheet, profit and loss account, dis closure of liabilities in the books of`
  line `accounts or any matter relating thereto.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where, in the case of 3 [a non - banking financial company], the auditor has made, or intends to`
  line `make, a report to the Bank under sub - section ( 1 ), he shall include in his rep ort under sub - section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 227 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), the contents of the report which he has made or`
  line `intends to make, to the Bank.]`
  line `2 [( 3 ) Where the bank is of the opinion that it is necessary so to do in the public interest or in the`
  line `interest of the non - banking financial company or in the interest of depositors of such company it may at`
  line `any time by order direct that a special audit of the accounts of the non - banking financial company in`
  line `relation to any such transaction or class of transactions or for such period or periods, as may be specified`
  line `in the order, shall be conducted and the Bank may appoint an auditor or auditors to conduct such special`
  line `audit and direct the auditor or the auditors to submit the report to it.`
  line `( 4 ) The rem uneration of the auditors as may be fixed by the Bank, having regard to the nature and`
  line `volume of work involved in the audit and the expenses of or incidental to the audit, shall be borne by the`
  line `non - banking financial company so audited.]`
  line `4 [ 4 5MAA. Power to t ake action against auditors. — Where any auditor fails to comply with any`
  line `direction given or order made by the Bank under section 45MA, the Bank, may, if satisfied, remove or`
  line `debar the auditor from exercising the duties as auditor of any of the Bank regulat ed entities for a`
  line `maximum period of three years, at a time.]`
  line `5 [ 45MB. Power of Bank to prohibit acceptance of deposit and alienation of assets. — ( 1 ) If any`
  line `non - banking financial company violates the provisions of any section or fails to comply with any`
  line `direc tion or order given by the Bank under any of the provisions of this Chapter, the Bank may prohibit`
  line `the non - banking financial company from accepting any deposit.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any agreement or instruments or any l aw`
  line `for the time being in force, the Bank, on being satisfied that it is necessary so to do in the public interest`
  line `or in the interest of the depositors, may direct, the non - banking financial company against which an order`
  line `prohibiting from accepting deposit has been issued, not to sell, transfer, create charge or mortgage or deal`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 19 (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 1997, s. 5 (w.e.f. 9 - 1 - 1997).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for “a non - banking institution, being a company” (w.e.f. 9 - 1 - 1997).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 139 (w.e.f. 9 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 1997, s. 6. (w.e.f. 9 - 1 - 1997).`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-47
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Page 47`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  sourcePage 47
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line 47
  line `in any manner with its property and assets without prior written permission of the Bank for such period`
  line `not exceeding six mon ths from the date of the order.`
  line `1 [ 45MBA. Resolution of non - banking financial company. — ( 1 ) Without prejudice to any other`
  line `provision of this Act or any other law for the time being in force, the Bank may, if it is satisfied, upon an`
  line `inspection of the Books of a non - banking financial company that it is in the pu blic interest or in the`
  line `interest of financial stability so to do for enabling the continuance of the activities critical to the`
  line `functioning of the financial system, frame schemes which may provide for any one or more of the`
  line `following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) amalgam ation with any other non - banking institution;`
  line `( b ) reconstruction of the non - banking financial company;`
  line `( c ) splitting the non - banking financial company into different units or institutions and vesting viable`
  line `and non - viable businesses in separate units or in stitutions to preserve the continuity of the activities of`
  line `that non - banking financial company that are critical to the functioning of the financial system and for`
  line `such purpose establish institutions called “ Bridge Institutions ”.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purpo ses of this sub - section, “ Bridge Institutions ” mean temporary`
  line `institutional arrangement made under the scheme referred to in this sub - section, to preserve the continuity`
  line `of the activities of a non - banking financial company that are critical to the function ing of the financial`
  line system.
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, the scheme referred to in`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) may provide for —`
  line `( a ) reduction of the pay and allowances of the chief executive officer, managing director,`
  line `chairman or any officer in the senior management of the non - banking financial company;`
  line `( b ) cancellation of all or some of the shares of the non - banking financial company held by the`
  line `chief executive officer, managing director, chairman or any offi cer in the senior management of the`
  line `non - banking financial company or their relatives;`
  line `( c ) sale of any of the assets of the non - banking financial company.`
  line `( 3 ) The chief executive officer, managing director, chairman or any officer in the senior management`
  line `of the non - banking financial company whose pay and allowances are reduced or the shareholders whose`
  line `shares are cancelled under the scheme shall not be entitl ed to any compensation.]`
  line `45MC. Power of Bank to file winding up petition. — ( 1 ) The Bank, on being satisfied that a non -`
  line `banking financial company —`
  line `( a ) is unable to pay its debt; or`
  line `( b ) has by virtue of the provisions of section 45 - IA become disqualified to carry on the business`
  line `of a non - banking financial institution; or`
  line `( c ) has been prohibited by the Bank from receiving deposit by an order and such order has been`
  line `in force for a period of not less than three months; or`
  line `( d ) the continuance of the non - banking f inancial company is detrimental to the public interest or`
  line `to the interest of depositors of the company,`
  line `may file an application for winding up of such non - banking financial company under the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956).`
  line `( 2 ) A non - banking financial comp any shall be deemed to be unable to pay its debt if it has refused or`
  line `has failed to meet within five working days any lawful demand made at any to its offices or branches and`
  line `the Bank certifies in writing that such company is unable to pay its debt.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 140 (w.e.f. 9 - 8 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-48
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Page 48`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  sourcePage 48
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line 48
  line `( 3 ) A copy of every application made by the Bank under sub - section ( 1 ) shall be sent to the Registrar`
  line `of Companies.`
  line `( 4 ) All the provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) relating to winding up of a company`
  line `shall apply to a winding up proceeding initiated on the application made by the Bank under this`
  line provision.]
  line `45N. Inspection. — 1 [( 1 ) The Bank may, at any time, cause an inspection to be made by one or more`
  line `of its officers or employees or other persons (hereafter in this section referred to as the inspecting`
  line `authority) —`
  line `( i ) of any non - banking institution, including a financial institution, for the purposes of verifying`
  line `the correctness or completeness of any statement, information or particulars furnished to the Bank or`
  line `for the purpose of obtaining any information or particulars which the non - banking institution has`
  line `failed to furnish on being called upon to do so; or`
  line `( ii ) of any non - banking institution being a financial institution, if the Bank considers i t necessary`
  line `or expedient to inspect that institution.]`
  line `( 2 ) It shall be the duly of every director or member of any committee or other body for the time being`
  line `vested with the management of the affairs of the non - banking institution or other officer or emplo yee`
  line `thereof to produce to the inspecting authority all such books, accounts and other documents in his custody`
  line `or power and to furnish that authority with any statements and information relating to the business of the`
  line `institution as that authority may requ ire of him, within such time as may be specified by that authority.`
  line `( 3 ) The inspecting authority may examine on oath any director or member of any committee or body`
  line `for the time being vested with the management of the affairs of the non - banking institution or other`
  line `officer or employee thereof, in relation to its business and may administer an oath accordingly.`
  line `2 [ 45NA. Deposits not to be solicited by unauthorised person. — No person shall solicit on behalf of`
  line `any non - banking institution either by publishing or causing to be published any prospectus or`
  line `advertisement or in any other manner deposits of money from the public unless —`
  line `( a ) he has been authorised in writing by the s aid non - banking institution to do so and specifies the`
  line `name of the institution which has so authorised him, and`
  line `( b ) the prospectus or advertisement complies with any order made by the Bank under section 45J`
  line `and with any other provision of law for the time being in force, applicable to the publication of such`
  line `prospectus or advertisement.]`
  line `3 [ 45NAA. Power in respect of group companies. — ( 1 ) The Bank may, at any time, direct a non -`
  line `banking financial company to annex to its financial statements or furnish separat ely, within such time and`
  line `at such intervals as may be specified by the Bank, such statements and information relating to the`
  line `business or affairs of any group company of the non - banking financial company as the Bank may`
  line `consider necessary or expedient to ob tain for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), the`
  line `Bank may, at any time, cause an inspection or audit to be made of any group company of a non - banking`
  line `financial company an d its books of account.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “ group company ” shall mean an arrangement involving two or more entities related to each`
  line `other through any of the following relationships, namely: —`
  line `( i ) subsidiary — parent (as may be notified by the Bank in accordance with Accounting`
  line `Standards);`
  line `( ii ) joint venture (as may be notified by the Bank in accordance with Accounting Standards);`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 20, for sub - section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 141 (w.e.f. 9 - 8 - 2019).`
