  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  sourcePage 49
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line 49
  line `( iii ) associate (as may be notified by the Bank in accordance with Accounting Standards);`
  line `( iv ) promoter - promotee (under the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of`
  line `1992) or the rules or regulations made there under for listed companies);`
  line `( v ) related party;`
  line `( vi ) common brand name (that is usage of a registered brand name of an entit y by another`
  line `entity for business purposes); and`
  line `( vii ) investment in equity shares of twenty per cent. and above in the entity;`
  line `( b ) “ Accounting Standards ” means the Accounting Standards notified by the Central`
  line `Government under section 133, read with section 469 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) and`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) of section 210A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).]`
  line `1 [ 45NB. Disclosure of information. — ( 1 ) Any information relating to a non - banking financial`
  line `company, —`
  line `( i ) contained in any statement or return submitted by such company under the provisions of this`
  line `chapter; or`
  line `( ii ) obtained through audit or inspection or otherwise by the Bank,`
  line `shall be treated as confidential and shall not, except otherwise provided in this section, be disclosed.`
  line `( 2 ) Noth ing in this section shall apply to —`
  line `( a ) the disclosure by any non - banking financial company, with the previous permission of the`
  line `Bank, of any information furnished to the Bank under sub - section ( 1 );`
  line `( b ) the publication by the Bank, if it considers necessary in the public interest so to do, of any`
  line `information collected by it under sub - section ( 1 ) in such consolidated form as it may think fit without`
  line `disclosing the name of any non - banking financial company or its borrowers;`
  line `( c ) the disclosure or publi cation by the non - banking financial company or by the Bank of any`
  line `such information to any other non - banking financial company or in accordance with the practice and`
  line `usage customary amongst such companies or as permitted or required under any other law:`
  line `Pro vided that any such information received by a non - banking financial company under this`
  line `clause shall not be published except in accordance with the practice and usage customary amongst`
  line `companies or as permitted or required under any other law.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithst anding anything contained in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force, the`
  line `Bank, if it is satisfied that, in the public interest or in the interest of the depositors or the non - banking`
  line `financial company or to prevent the affairs of any non - banking financial company being conducted in a`
  line `manner detrimental to the interest of the depositors, it is expedient so to do, may, either on its own motion`
  line `or on being requested, furnish or communicate any information relating to the conduct of business b y any`
  line `non - banking financial company to any authority constituted under any law.`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, no court or tribunal or`
  line `other authority shall compel the Bank to produce or to give inspection of any statement or other material`
  line `obtained by the Bank under any provisions of this chapter.]`
  line `45NC. Power of Bank to exempt. — The Bank, on being satisfied that it is necessary so to do, may`
  line `declare by notification in the Official Gazette that any or all of t he provisions of this Chapter shall not`
  line `apply to a non - banking institution or a class of non - banking institutions or a non - banking financial`
  line `company or to any class or non - banking financial companies either generally or for such period as may be`
  line `specified, subject to such conditions, limitations or restrictions as it may think fit to impose.]`
  line `45 - O. [ Penalties ]. — Omitted by the Reserve Bank of India ( Amendment ) Act, 1974, (51 of 1974),`
  line `s. 22 ( w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `45P. [ Cognizance of offence ]. — Omitted by s. 22, ibid. ( w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974)`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 1997, s. 7 (w.e.f. 9 - 1 - 1997).`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
