  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  sourcePage 50
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line 50
  line `45Q. Chapter IIIB to override other laws. — The provisions of this Chapter shall have effect`
  line `notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or`
  line `any instrument having effect by virtue of any such law.]`
  line `1 [ 45QA. Power of Company Law Board to offer repayment of deposit. — ( 1 ) Every deposit`
  line `accepted by a non - banking financial company, unless renewed, shall be repaid in accordance with the`
  line `terms and condition of such deposit.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a non - banking financial company has failed to repay and deposit or part thereof in`
  line `accordance with the terms and conditions of such deposit, the Company Law Board constituted`
  line `under section 10E of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), may, if it is satisfied, either on its own motion`
  line `or on an application of the depositor, t hat it is necessary so to do to safeguard the interests of the`
  line `company, the depositors or in the public interest, direct, by order, the non - banking financial company to`
  line `make repayment of such deposit or part thereof forthwith or within such time and subjec t to such`
  line `conditions as may be specified in the order:`
  line `Provided that the Company Law Board may, before making any order under this sub - section, give a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard to the non - banking financial company and the other pe rsons`
  line `interest ed in the matter.`
  line `45QB. Nomination by depositors. — ( 1 ) Where a deposit is held by a non - banking financial`
  line `institution to the credit of one or more persons, the depositor or, as the case may be, all the depositors`
  line `together may nominate, in the manner prescri bed by rules made by the Central Government under section`
  line `45ZA of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), one person to whom in the event of the death of`
  line `the sole depositor or the death of all the depositors, the amount of deposit may be returned by the non -`
  line `banking financial institution.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, or in any`
  line `disposition, whether testamentary or otherwise, in respect of such deposit, where a nomination made`
  line `purports to confer on any person the right to receive the amount of deposit from the non - banking financial`
  line `institution, the nominee shall, on the death of the sole depositor or, as the case may be, on the death of all`
  line `the depositors, become entitled to all the rights of the so le depositor or, as the case may be, of the`
  line `depositors, in relation to such deposit to the exclusion of all other persons, unless the nomination is varied`
  line `or cancelled in the manner prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under section 45ZA of`
  line `t he Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949).`
  line `( 3 ) Where the nominee is a minor, it shall be lawful for the depositor making the nomination to`
  line `appoint, in the manner prescribed by rules made by the Central Government under section 45ZA of the`
  line `Banking Regula tion Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), any person to receive the amount of deposit in the event of`
  line `his death during the minority of the nominee.`
  line `( 4 ) Payment by a non - banking institution in accordance with the provisions of this section shall`
  line `constitute a full discha rge to the non - banking institution of its liability in respect of the deposit:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub - section shall effect the right or claim which any person`
  line `may have against the person to whom any payment is made under this section.`
  line `( 5 ) No notice of the claim of any person, other than the person or persons in whose name a deposit is`
  line `held by a non - banking institution, shall be receivable by the non - banking institution, nor shall the non -`
  line `banking institution be bound by any such notice e ven though expressly given to it:`
  line `Provided that where any decree order, certificate or other authority from a court of competent`
  line `jurisdiction relating to such deposit is produced before a non - banking institution, the non - banking`
  line `institution shall take due note of such decree, order, certificate or other authority.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 1997, s. 8 (w.e.f. 9 - 1 - 1997).`
