obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line 51
  line `1 [CHAPTER IIIC`
  line `P ROHINITION OF ACCEPTANCE OF DEPOSITS BY UNINCORPORATED BODIES`
  line `45R. Interpretation. — The words and expressions used in this Chapter and defined in Chapter IIIB`
  line `shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them therein.`
  line `2 [ 45S. Deposits not to be accepted in certain cases. — ( 1 ) No person, being an individual or a firm`
  line `or an unincorporated association of indivi duals shall, accept any deposit —`
  line `( i ) if his or its business wholly o r partly includes any of the activities specified in clause ( c ) of`
  line `section 45 - 1; or`
  line `( ii ) if his or its principal business is that of receiving of deposits under any scheme or`
  line `arrangement or in any other manner or lending in any manner:`
  line `Provided that nothin g contained in this sub - section shall apply to the receipt of money by an`
  line `individual by way of loan from any of his relatives or to the receipt of money by a firm by way of`
  line `loan from the relative or relatives of any of the partners.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any person referred to in sub - section ( 1 ) holds any deposit on the 1st day of April, 1997`
  line `which is not in accordance with sub - section ( 1 ), such deposit shall be repaid by that person immediately`
  line `after such deposit becomes due for repayment or within three years from the date of such commencement,`
  line `whichever is earlier:`
  line `Provided that if the Bank is satisfied on an application made by any person to the Bank that such`
  line `person is unable to repay a part of the deposits for reasons beyond his control or such repayment shall`
  line `c ause extreme hardship to him, it may, by an order in writing, extend such period by a period not`
  line `exceeding one year subject to such conditions as may be specified in the order.`
  line `( 3 ) on and from the date of 1st day of April, 1997, no person referred to in su b - section ( 1 ) shall issue`
  line `or cause to be issued any advertisement in any form for soliciting deposit.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, a person shall be deemed to be a relat ive of another`
  line `if, and only if, —`
  line `( i ) they are members of a Hindu undivided family; or`
  line `( ii ) they are husband and wife; or`
  line `( iii ) the one is related to the other in the manner indicated in the List of Relatives below: —`
  line `List of Relatives`
  line `1. Father, 2. Mother (including step - mother), 3.Son (including stepson), 4. Son ’ s wife,`
  line `5. Daughter (including step - daughter), 6. Father ’ s father, 7. Father ’ s mother,`
  line `8. Mother ’ s mother, 9. Mother ’ s father, 10. Son ’ s son, 11. Son ’ s son ’ s wife, 12. Son ’ s`
  line `Daughter 13. Son ’ s Daughter ’ s husband, 14. Daughter ’ s husband, 15. Daughter ’ s son,`
  line `16. Daughter ’ s son ’ s wife, 17. Daughter ’ s daughter, 18. Daughter ’ s daughter ’ s`
  line `husband. 19. Brother (including step - brother), 20. Brother ’ s wife, 21. Sister (including`
  line `step - sister), 22. Sister ’ s husband].`
  line `45T. Power to issue search warrants. — ( 1 ) Any court having jurisdiction to issue a search warrant`
  line `under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), may, on an application by an officer of the bank`
  line `or of the State Government authorised in this behalf stating his belief that certain docu ments relating to`
  line `acceptance of deposits in contravention of the provisions of section 45S are secreted in any place within`
  line `the local limits of the jurisdiction of such court, issue a warrant to search for such documents.`
  line `( 2 ) A warrant issued under sub - sec tion ( 1 ) shall be executed in the same manner and shall have the`
  line `same effect as a search warrant issued under the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 10 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 1984).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 1997, s. 9, for section 45S (w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1997).`
