obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line 52
  line `1 [ CHAPTER IIID`
  line `R EGULATION OF TRANSACTIONS IN DERIVATIVES, MONEY MARKET INSTRUMENTS, SECURITIES, ETC.`
  line `45U. Definitions. — For the purposes of this Chapter, —`
  line `( a ) “ derivative ” means an instrument, to be settled at a future date, whose value is derived from`
  line `change in interest rate, foreign exchange rate, credit rating or credit index, price of securities (also`
  line `called “ underlying ” ), or a combination of more than one of them and i ncludes interest rate swaps,`
  line `forward rate agreements, foreign currency swaps, foreign currency - rupee swaps, foreign currency`
  line `options, foreign currency - rupee options or such other instruments as may be specified by the Bank`
  line `from time to time;`
  line `( b ) “ money mar ket instruments ” include call or notice money, term money, repo, reverse repo,`
  line `certificate of deposit, commercial usance bill, commercial paper and such other debt instrument of`
  line `original or initial maturity up to one year as the Bank may specify from time to time;`
  line `( c ) “ repo ” means an instrument for borrowing funds by selling securities with an agreement to`
  line `repurchase the securities on a mutually agreed future date at an agreed price which includes interest`
  line `for the funds borrowed;`
  line `( d ) “ reverse repo ” means an instrument for lending funds by purchasing securities with an`
  line `agreement to resell the securities on a mutually agreed future date at an agreed price which includes`
  line `interest for the funds lent;`
  line `( e ) “ securities ” means securities of the Central Government or a State Government or such`
  line `securities of a local authority as may be specified in this behalf by the Central Government and, for`
  line `the purposes of “ repo ” or “ reverse repo ”, include corporate bonds and debentures.`
  line `45V. Transactions in derivatives. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Securities`
  line `Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956(42 of 1956) or any other law for the time being in force, transactions in`
  line `such derivatives, as may be specified by the Bank from time to time, shall be valid, if at least one of the`
  line `parties to the transaction is the Bank, a scheduled bank, or such other agency falling under the regulatory`
  line `purview of the Bank under the Act, the Banking Regulation Act, 1949(10 of 1949), the Foreign Exchange`
  line `Management Act, 1999(42 of 1999), or any other Act or instrument having the force of law, as may be`
  line `specified by the Bank from time to time.`
  line `( 2 ) Transactions in such derivatives, as had been specified by the Bank from time to time, shall be`
  line `deemed always to have been valid, as if the provi sions of sub - section ( 1 ) were in force at all material`
  line times.
  line `45W. Power to regulate transactions in derivatives, money market instruments, etc. — ( 1 ) The`
  line `Bank may, in public interest, or to regulate the financial system of the country to its advantage, dete rmine`
  line `the policy relating to interest rates or interest rate products and give directions in that behalf to all`
  line `agencies or any of them, dealing in securities, money market instruments, foreign exchange, derivatives,`
  line `or other instruments of like nature as the Bank may specify from time to time:`
  line `Provided that the directions issued under this sub - section shall not relate to the procedure for`
  line `execution or settlement of the trades in respect of the transactions mentioned therein, on the Stock`
  line `Exchanges recognised under section 4 of the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956(42 of 1956).`
  line `( 2 ) The Bank may, for the purpose of enabling it to regulate agencies referred to in sub - section ( 1 ),`
  line `call for any information, statement or other particulars from t hem, or cause an inspection of such agencies`
  line `to be made.`
  line `45X. Duty to comply with directions and furnish information. — It shall be the duty of every`
  line `director or member or other body for the time being vested with the management of the affairs of the`
  line `agencie s referred to in section 45W to comply with the directions given by the Bank and to submit the`
  line `information or statement or particulars called for under that section. ]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2006, s. 4 ( w.e.f. 9 - 1 - 2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  kind page
