obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line 53
  line `1 [CHAPTER IIIE`
  line `J OINT M ECHANISM`
  line `45Y. Joint Mechanism. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India Act, 1992(15 of 1992) or any other law for the time being in force, if any`
  line `difference o f opinion arises as to whether —`
  line `( i ) any instrument, being derivative referred to in clause ( a ) or mon ey market instrument referred`
  line `to in clause ( b ) or repo referred to in clause ( c ) or reverse repo referred to in clause ( d ) or securities`
  line `referred to in clause ( e ) of section 45U of this Act; or`
  line `( ii ) any instrument, being policy of life insurance under the Insurance Act, 1938(4 of 1938), or`
  line `the rules or regulations made thereunder, or, scrips or any other securities referred to in sub - clauses`
  line `( i ), ( ia ), ( ib), ( ic ), ( id ), ( ie ), ( ii ), ( iia ) and ( iii ) of clause ( h ) of section 2 of the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956(42 of 1956),`
  line `is hybrid or composite instrument, having a component of money market investment or securities market`
  line `instrument or a component of insurance or any other instrument referred to in clause ( i ) or clause ( ii ) and`
  line `falls with in the jurisdiction of the Reserve Bank of India or the Securities and Exchange Board of India`
  line `established under section 3 of the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992(15 of 1992) or the`
  line `Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority established under section 3 of the Insurance Regulatory`
  line `and Development Authority Act, 1999(41 of 1999) or the Pension Fund Regulatory and Development`
  line `Authority constituted by the Resolution of the Government of India number F.No. 1(6)2007 - PR, dated the`
  line `14th November, 2008, such difference of opinion shall be referred to a Joint Committee consis ting of the`
  line `following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the Union Finance Minister — ex officio Chairperson;`
  line `( b ) the Go vernor, Reserve Bank of India — ex officio Vice - Chairperson;`
  line `( c ) the Secretary, D epartment of Economic Affairs in the Ministry of Finance, Government of`
  line `India — ex officio Member;`
  line `( d ) the Secretary, Department of Financial Services in the Ministry of Finance, Government of`
  line `India — ex officio Member;`
  line `( e ) the Chairperson, Insurance Regulator y and Development Authority — ex officio Member;`
  line `( f ) the Chairman, Securitie s and Exchange Board of India — ex officio Member;`
  line `( g ) the Chairperson, Pension Fund Regulatory and Development Authority — ex officio Member.`
  line `( 2 ) The Secretary, Department of Financial Services in the Ministry of Finance, Government of India`
  line `shall be the convener of the meetings of the Joint Committee referred to in sub - section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 3 ) In case of any difference of opinion referred to in sub - section ( 1 ), any Member of the Joint`
  line `Committee referred to in clauses ( b ), ( e ), ( f ) or ( g ) of that sub - section may make a reference to the Joint`
  line Committee.
  line `( 4 ) The Joint Committee shall follow such procedure as it may consider expedient and give, within a`
  line `period of three months from the date of reference made under sub - section ( 3 ), its decisions thereon to the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line `( 5 ) The decision of the Joint Committee shall be binding on the Reserve Bank of India, the Securities`
  line `and Exchange Board of India, the Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority and the Pension`
  line `Fund Regulatory and Development Authority.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 2010, s. 2 (w.e.f. 18 - 6 - 2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-54
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Page 54`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  sourcePage 54
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line 54
  line `1 [ CHAPTER IIIF`
  line `M ONETARY P OLICY`
  line `45Z. Provisions of this Chapter to override other provisions of Act. — The provisions of this`
  line `Chapter shall have effect, notwithstanding anyth ing inconsistent therewith contained in an y other`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line `45ZA. Inflation targe t. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall, in consultation with the Bank,`
  line `determine the inflation target in terms of the Consumer Price Index, once in every five years.`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government shall, upon such determination, notify the inflation target in the Official`
  line Gazette.
  line `45ZB. Constitution of Monetary Policy Committee. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, constitute a Co mmittee to be called the Monetary Policy Committee`
  line `of the Bank.`
  line `( 2 ) The Monetary Policy Committee shall consist of the following Members, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the Governor of the Bank — Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line `( b ) Deputy Governor of the Bank, in charge of Monetary Policy — Member, ex officio;`
  line `( c ) one officer of the Bank to be nominated by the Central Board — Member, ex officio; and`
  line `( d ) three persons to be appoi nted by the Central Government — Members.`
  line `( 3 ) The Monetary Policy Committee shall determine the Policy Rate requi red to achieve the inflation`
  line target.
  line `( 4 ) The decision of the Monetary Policy Committe e shall be binding on the Bank.`
  line `45ZC. Eligibility and selection of Members appointed by Central Government. — ( 1 ) The`
  line `Members of the Monetary Policy Committee referred to in clause ( d ) of sub - section ( 2 ) of section 45ZB`
  line `shall be appointed by the Central Government from amongst persons of ability, integrity and standing,`
  line `having knowledge and experience in the field of economics or banking or finance or monetary policy:`
  line `Provide d that no person shall be appointed as a Member, in case such person —`
  line `( i ) has completed the age of seventy years on the date of appointment as Member;`
  line `( ii ) is a Member of any Board or Committee of the Bank;`
  line `( iii ) is an employee of the Bank;`
  line `( iv ) is a publi c servant as defined under section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860);`
  line `( v ) is a Member of Parliament or any State Legislature;`
  line `( vi ) has been at any time, adjudged as an insolvent;`
  line `( vii ) has been convicted of an offence which is punishable with an imp risonment for a term of one`
  line `hundred and eighty days or more;`
  line `( viii ) is physically or mentally incapable of discharging the duties of a Member of the Monetary`
  line `Policy Committee; or`
  line `( ix ) has a material conflict of interest with the Bank and is unable to resol ve such conflict.`
  line `( 2 ) The Members of the Monetary Policy Committee referred to in clause ( d ) of sub - section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 45ZB shall be appointed by the Central Government on the recommendations made by Search -`
  line `cum - Selection Committee consisting of the fol lowing members, namely: —`
  line `( a ) Cabinet Secretary — Chairperson;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 222 (w.e.f. 27 - 6 - 2016).`
