  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  sourcePage 55
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line 55
  line `( b ) Governor of the Reserve Bank of India or his representative (not bel ow the rank of Deputy`
  line `Governor) — member;`
  line `( c ) Secretary, Department of Economic Affairs — member;`
  line `( d ) three experts in the field of economics or banking or finance or Monetary policy to be`
  line `nominated by the Central Government — members.`
  line `( 3 ) While selecting the Members of the Monetary Policy Committee, the Search - cum - Selection`
  line `Committee shall follow such procedure as may be prescr ibed by the Central Government.`
  line `45ZD. Terms and conditions of appointment of Members of Monetary Policy Committee. — ( 1 )`
  line `The Members of the Monetary Policy Committee appointed under clause ( d ) of sub - section ( 2 ) of section`
  line `45ZB shall hold office for a period of four years and shall not be eligible for re - appointment.`
  line `( 2 ) The terms and conditions of appointment of Members of the Monetary Policy Committee shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed by the Central Government and the remuneration and other allowances payable`
  line `to such Members shall be such as may be specified by the regulations made by the Central Board.`
  line `( 3 ) A Member may resign from the Monetary Policy Committee, at any time before the expiry of his`
  line `tenure under sub - section ( 1 ), by giving to the Central Governme nt, a written notice of not less than six`
  line `weeks, and on the acceptance of the resignation by the Central Government, he shall cease to be a`
  line `Member of the Monetary Polic y Committee.`
  line `45ZE. Removal of Members of Monetary Policy Committee. — ( 1 ) The Central Gove rnment may`
  line `remove from office any Member of the Monetary Policy Committee appointed under clause ( d ) of sub -`
  line `se ction ( 2 ) of section 45ZB, who —`
  line `( a ) is, or at any time has been, adjudged as an insolvent; or`
  line `( b ) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as a Member; or`
  line `( c ) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line `( d ) has failed to adequately disclose any material conflict of interest at the time of his`
  line `appointment; or`
  line `( e ) does no t attend three consecutive meetings of the Monetary Policy Committee without`
  line `obtaining prior leave; or`
  line `( f ) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as a`
  line `Member; or`
  line `( g ) has acquired any post referred t o in clauses ( ii ), ( iii ), ( iv ) and clause ( v ) of the proviso to sub -`
  line `section ( 1 ) of section 45ZC; or`
  line `( h ) has, in the opinion of the Central Government, so abused his position as to render his`
  line `continuance in office detrimental to the public interest.`
  line `( 2 ) No Member appointed under clause ( d ) of sub - section ( 2 ) of section 45ZB shall be removed under`
  line `clause ( d ) or clause ( e ) or clause ( f ) or clause ( g ) or clause ( h ) of sub - section ( 1 ) unless he has been given`
  line `a reasonable opportunit y of being heard in the matter.`
  line `45ZF. Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of Monetary Policy Committee. — No act or`
  line `proceeding of the Monetary Policy Committee shall be invalid merely by reason of —`
  line `( a ) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of the Monetary Pol icy Committee; or`
  line `( b ) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a Member of the Monetary Policy`
  line `Committee; or`
  line `( c ) any irregularity in the procedure of the Monetary Policy Committee not af fecting the merits of`
  line `the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-56
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Page 56`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  sourcePage 56
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line 56
  line `45ZG. Secretary to Monetary Policy Committee. — ( 1 ) The Bank shall appoint a Secretary to the`
  line `Monetary Policy Committee to provide secretariat support to the said Committee.`
  line `( 2 ) The Secretary shall perform such functions and in such manner as may be specified by the`
  line `regulat ions made b y the Central Board.`
  line `45ZH. Information for Monetary Policy Committee Members. — ( 1 ) The Bank shall provide all`
  line `information to the Members of the Monetary Policy Committee that may be relevant to achieve the`
  line `inflation target.`
  line `( 2 ) In addition to information pr ovided by the Bank under sub - section ( 1 ), any Member of the`
  line `Monetary Policy Committee may, at any time, request the Bank for additional information, including any`
  line `data, models or analysis.`
  line `( 3 ) The Bank shall provide the information, as referred to in sub - s ection ( 2 ), to the Member of the`
  line `Monetary Policy Committee, within reasonable time, unless —`
  line `( a ) the information pertains to an entity or person and is not publicly available; or`
  line `( b ) the information allows an entity or person to be identified and the information is not publicly`
  line available.
  line `( 4 ) Any information provided by the Bank to a Member of the Monetary Policy Committee shall be`
  line `provided to all the Members of the Mone tary Policy Committee.`
  line `45Z - I. Meetings of Monetary Policy Committee. — ( 1 ) The Bank shall organise at least four`
  line `meetings of the Monetary Policy Committee in a year.`
  line `( 2 ) The meeting schedule of the Monetary Policy Committee for a year shall be published by the`
  line `Bank at least one week before the first meeting in that year.`
  line `( 3 ) Th e meetin g schedule may be changed only —`
  line `( a ) by way of a decision taken at a prior meeting of the Monetary Policy Committee; or`
  line `( b ) if, in the opinion of the Governor, an additional meeting is required or a meeting is required to`
  line `be rescheduled due to admin istrative exigencies.`
  line `( 4 ) Any change in meeting schedule shall be published by the Bank as soon as practicable.`
  line `( 5 ) The quorum for a meeting of the Monetary Policy Committee shall be four Members, at least one`
  line `of whom shall be the Governor and in his absen ce, the Deputy Governor who is the Member of the`
  line `Monetary Policy Committee.`
  line `( 6 ) The meetings of the Monetary Policy Committee shall be presided over by the Governor, and in`
  line `his absence by the Deputy Governor who is a Member of the Monetary Policy Committee.`
  line `( 7 ) Each Member of the Monetary Policy Committee shall have one vote.`
  line `( 8 ) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Monetary Policy Committee shall be`
  line `decided by a majority of votes by the Members present and voting, and in the event of an eq uality of`
  line `votes, the Governor shall have a second or casting vote.`
  line `( 9 ) The Central Government may, if it considers necessary, convey its views in writing to the`
  line `Monetary Policy Committee from time to time.`
  line `( 10 ) The vote of each Member of the Monetary Polic y Committee for a proposed resolution shall be`
  line `recorded against such Member.`
  line `( 11 ) Each Member of the Monetary Policy Committee shall write a statement specifying the reasons`
  line `for voting in favour of, or against the proposed resolution.`
  line `duct, code of confide ntiality and any other incidental matter for the functioning of the Monetary`
  line `Policy Committee shall be such as may be specified by the regulations made by the Central Board.`
