  sourcePage 57
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line 57
  line `( 13 ) The proceeding of the Monetary Policy C ommittee shall be confidential.`
  line `45ZJ. Steps to be taken to implement decision of Monetary Policy Committee. — ( 1 ) The Bank`
  line `shall publish a document explaining the steps to be taken by it to implement the decisions of the`
  line `Monetary Policy Committee, including any changes thereto.`
  line `( 2 ) The particulars to be included in such document and the frequency of publications of such`
  line `document shall be such as may be specified by the regulations made by the Central Board.`
  line `45ZK. Publication of decisions. — The Bank shall publish, after the conclusion of every meeting of`
  line `the Monetary Policy Committee, the resolution adopted by the said Committee;`
  line `45ZL. Publication of proceedings of meeting of Monetary Policy Committee. — The Bank shall`
  line `publish, on the fourteenth day after every meeting of the Monetary Policy Committee, the minutes of the`
  line `proceedings of the meeting which shall include the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the resolution adopted at the meeting of the Monetary Policy Committee;`
  line `( b ) the vote of each member of the Monetary Policy Committee, ascribed to such member, on`
  line `resolutions adopted in the said meeting; and`
  line `( c ) the statement of each member of the Monetary Policy Committee under sub - section ( 11 ) of`
  line `section 45ZL on the resolutio ns adopted in the said meeting.`
  line `45ZM. Monetary Policy Report. — ( 1 ) The Bank sha ll, once in every six months, publish a`
  line `document to be called the Mone tary Policy Report, explaining —`
  line `( a ) the sources of inflation; and`
  line `( b ) the forecasts of inflation for the period between six to eighteen months from the date of`
  line `publication of the documen t.`
  line `( 2 ) The form and contents of the Monetary Policy Report shall be such as may be specified by the`
  line `regulat ions made by the Central Board.`
  line `45ZN. Failure to maintain inflation target. — Where the Bank fails to meet the inflation target, it`
  line `shall set out in a re port to the Central Government —`
  line `( a ) the reasons for failure to achieve the inflation target;`
  line `( b ) remedial actions proposed to be taken by the Bank; and`
  line `( c ) an estimate of the time - period within which the inflation target shall be achieved pursuant to`
  line `tim ely implementation of proposed remedial actions.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the factors that constitute failure shall be such as may`
  line `be notified by the Central Government in the Official Gazette, within three months from the date of the`
  line `commencement of Part I of Chapte r XII of the Finance Act, 2016.`
  line `45ZO. Power to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line `( 2 ) In particula r and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing pow er, such rules may`
  line `provide for —`
  line `( a ) the procedure of functioning of the Search - cum - Selection Committee under sub - section ( 3 ) of`
  line `section 45ZC;`
  line `( b ) the terms and conditions of appointment, (other than the remuneration and other allowances),`
  line `of Members of the Monetary Policy Committee under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 45ZD; and`
  line `( c ) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed by the Central Government by rules.]`
