obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line 58
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `G ENERAL PROVISIONS`
  line `46. Contribution by Central Government to the Reserve Fund. — The 1 [Central Government]`
  line `shall transfer to the Bank rupee securities to the value of five crores of rupees to be allocated by the Bank`
  line `to the Reserve Fund.`
  line `2 [ 46A. Contribution to National Rural Credit (Long Term Operations) Fund and National`
  line `Rural Credit (Stabilisation) Fund. — The Bank shall contribute every year such sums of money as it`
  line `may consider necessary and feasible to do so, to the National Rural Credit (Long Term Operations) Fund`
  line `and the National Rural Credit (Stabilisation) Fund established and maintained by the National Bank under`
  line `sections 42 and 43, respectively, of the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development Act, 1981`
  line `(61 of 1981).]`
  line `3 [ 46C. National Industrial Credit (Long Term Operations) Fund. — ( 1 ) The Bank shall establish`
  line `and maintain a Fund to be known as the National Industrial Credit (Long Term Operations) Fund to`
  line `which shall be credited —`
  line `( a ) an initial sum of ten crores of rupees by the Bank;`
  line `( b ) such further sums of money as the Bank may contribute every year:`
  line `Provided that the annual contribution during each of the five years commencing with the year`
  line `ending on the 30th day of June, 1965 shall not be less than five crores of rupees:`
  line `Provided further that the Central Government may, if the circumstances so require, authorise the`
  line `Bank to reduce the said sum of five crores of rupees in any year.`
  line `( 2 ) The amount in the said fund shall be applied by the Bank only to the following objects, n amely: —`
  line `4 * * * * * ]`
  line `5 [( c ) the making to the Exim Bank 6 [or the Reconstruction Bank 7 [or the Small Industries Bank`
  line `8 [ or the National Bank for Financing Infrastructure and Development or the other`
  line `development financial institution ] ], as the case may be] of loans and advances for the purposes of`
  line `any business of the Exim Bank 6 [or the Reconstruction Bank 7 [or the Small Industries Bank 8 [ or the`
  line `National Bank for Financing Infrastructure and Development or the other development`
  line `financial institu tion, ] ] as the case may be];`
  line `( d ) the purchasing of bonds and debentures issued by the Exim Bank 6 [or the Reconstruction`
  line `Bank 7 [or the Small Industries Bank 8 [ or the National Bank for Financing Infrastructure and`
  line `Development or the other development financial institution, ] ] as the case may be ].]`
  line `9 [ 46D. National Housing Credit (Long Term Operations) Fund. — ( 1 ) The Bank shall establish and`
  line `maintain a Fund to be known as the National Housing Credit (Long Term Operations) Fund to which`
  line `shall be credited ev ery year such sums of money as it may consider necessary.`
  line `( 2 ) The amount in the said Fund shall be applied by the Bank only t o the following objects namely: —`
  line `( a ) the making to the National Housing Bank of loans and advances for the purpose of any`
  line `business of the National Housing Bank;`
  line `( b ) the purchasing of bonds and debentures issued by the National Housing Bank.]`
  line `10 [ 47. Allocation of surplus profits. — After making provision for bad and doubtful debts,`
  line `depreciation in assets, contributions to staff and superannuation fund 11 [and for all other matters for which`
  line `provision is to be made by or under this Act or which ] are usually provided for by bankers, the balance, of`
  line `the profits shall be paid to the Central Government.]`
  line `1. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.”.`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 61 of 1981, s. 61 and the Second Schedule, for sections 46A and 46B (w. e.f. 12 - 7 - 1982). Earlier these`
  line `sections were inserted by Act 24 of 1955, s. 7 (w.e.f. 8 - 5 - 1955).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 18 of 1964, s. 38 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 7 - 1964).`
  line `4. Clauses ( a ) and ( b ) omitted by Act 53 of 2003, s. 12 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 2 - 7 - 2004).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 28 of 1981, s. 40 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1982).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 62 of 1984, s. 71 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 20 - 3 - 1985).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 39 of 1989, s. 53 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 7 - 3 - 1990).`
  line `8.Ins. by Act 17 of 2021, s. 47 and the second schedule (w.e.f. 19 - 4 - 2021).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 53 of 1987, s. 56 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 9 - 7 - 1988).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule, for section 47 (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 24 of 1955, s. 8, for “and such other contingencies as” (w.e.f. 8 - 5 - 1955).`
