obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line 59
  line `48. Exemption of Banks from income - t ax and super - tax. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in 1 [ the Income - tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961)] or any other enactment for the time being in force relating to`
  line `income - tax or super - tax, the bank shall not be liable to pay income - tax or super - tax on any of its income,`
  line `profits or gains.`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `49. Publication of Bank rate. — The Bank shall make public from time to time the standard rate at`
  line `which it is prepared to buy or re - discount bills of exchange or other commercial paper el igible for`
  line `purchase under this Act.`
  line `4 [ 50. Auditors. — ( 1 ) Not less than two auditors shall be appointed, and their remuneration fixed, by`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line `( 2 ) The auditors shall hold office for such term not exceeding one year as the Central Government`
  line `may fix while appointing them, and shall be eligible for re - appointment.]`
  line `51. Appointment of special auditors by Government. — Without prejudice to anything conta ined in`
  line `section 50, the 5 [Central Government] may at any time appoint the 6 [Comptroller and Auditor - General]`
  line `7 *** to examine and report upon the accounts of the Bank.`
  line `52. Powers and duties of auditors. — ( 1 ) Every auditor shall be supplied with a copy of the annual`
  line `balance - sheet, and it shall be his duty to examine the same, together with the accounts and vouchers`
  line `relating thereto; and every auditor shall have a list delivered to him of all books kept by the Bank, and`
  line `shall at all reasonable time have acce ss to the books, accounts and other documents of the Bank, and may`
  line `at the expense of the Bank 8 *** employ accountants or other person to assist him in investigating such`
  line `accounts, and may, in relation to such accounts, examine any Director or officer of the Bank.`
  line `( 2 ) Th e auditors shall make a report 9 *** to the 5 [Central Government] 10 *** upon the annua l`
  line `balance - sheet and accounts, and in every such report they shall state whether, in their opinion, the`
  line `balance - sheet is a full and fair balance - sheet containing all necessary particulars and properly drawn up so`
  line `as to exhibit a true and correct view of the state of the Bank ’ s affairs, and, in case they have called for any`
  line `explanation or information from the Central Board, whether it has been given and whether it is`
  line `satisfactory. 11 ***.`
  line `53. Returns. — ( 1 ) The Bank shall prepare and transmit to the 5 [Central Government] a weekly`
  line `account of the Issue Department and of the Banking Department in 12 [such] form as the 5 [Central`
  line `Government] may, by notification in the Gazette of India, prescribe. The 5 [Central Government] shall`
  line `cause these accounts to be 13 [published i n the Gazette of India at such intervals and in such modified form`
  line `as it may deem fit].`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1978, s. 9, for “Indian Income - tax Act, 1922” (w.e.f. 21 - 7 - 1978).`
  line `2. The proviso omitted by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `3. Sub - sec tion ( 2 ) omitted by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule, for section 50 (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `5. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.”.`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 32 of 1951, s. 18, for “Auditor General” ( w.e.f. 1 - 11 - 1951).`
  line `7. The words “or such auditors as it thinks fit” omitted by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `8. The words “if appointed by it or at the expense of the Central Government if appointed by that Government” omitted by`
  line `Act 24 of 1955, s. 9 (w.e.f. 8 - 5 - 1955).`
  line `9. The words “to the shareholders or” omitted by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `10. The words “as the case may be” omitted by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `11. Th e words “Any such report made to the shareholders shall be read, together with the report of the Central Board, at the`
  line `annual general meeting” omitted by s. 7 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `12. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for certain words`
  line `1 3. Subs. by Act 24 of 1978, s. 9, for “published weekly in the Government of India” (w.e.f. 21 - 7 - 1978).`
