obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line 60
  line `( 2 ) The Batik shall also, within two months from the date on which the annual accounts of the Bank`
  line `are closed, transmit to the 1 [Central Government] a copy of the ann ual accounts signed by the Governor,`
  line `the Deputy Governors and the Chief Accounting Officer of the Bank, and certified by the auditors,`
  line `together with a report by the Central Board on the working of the Bank throughout the year, and the`
  line `1 [Central Government] shall cause such accounts and report to be published in the Gazette of India.`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 [ 54. Rural Credit and Development. — The Bank may maintain expert staff to study various aspects`
  line `of rural credit and develo pment and in particular it may: —`
  line `( a ) tender expert guidance and assistance to the National Bank;`
  line `( b ) conduct special studies in such areas as it may consider necessary to do so for promoting`
  line `integrated rural development.]`
  line `4 [ 54A. Delegation of powers. — ( 1 ) The Governor may, by general or speci al order, delegate to a`
  line `Deputy Governor, subjects to such conditions and limitations, if any, as may be specified in the order,`
  line `such of the powers and functions exercisable by him 5 *** under this Act or under any other law for the`
  line `time being in force as he may deem necessary for the efficient administration of the functions of the`
  line Bank.
  line `( 2 ) The fact that a Deputy Governor exercises any power or does any act or thing in pursuance of this`
  line `Act shall be conclusive proof of his authority to do so.]`
  line `6 [ 54AA. Power of Bank to depute its employees to other institutions. — 7 [( 1 ) The Bank may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any law, or in any agreement, for the time being in force, depute`
  line `any member of its staff for s uch period as it may think fit, —`
  line `( a ) to any ins titution which is wholly or substantially owned by the Bank;`
  line `( b ) to the Development Bank, so, however, that no such deputation shall continue after the`
  line `expiration of thirty months from the commencement of section 5 of the Public Financial Institutions`
  line `Laws (Amendment) Act, 1975 (52 of 1975);`
  line `( c ) to the Unit Trust, so, however, that no such deputation shall continue after the expiration of`
  line `thirty months from the date notified by the Central Government under sub - section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `4A of the Unit Trust of India Act, 1963 (52 of 1963);`
  line `and thereupon the person so deputed shall, during the period of his deputation, render such service to the`
  line `institution to which he is so deputed as that institution may require.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where a person has been deputed to an insti tution under sub - section ( 1 ), he shall not be entitled to`
  line `claim any salary, emoluments and other terms and conditions of service which he would not have been`
  line `entitled to claim if he had not been so deputed.`
  line `( 3 ) Nothing contained in this section shall empower the Bank to depute any member of its staff to any`
  line `institution on any salary, emoluments or other terms and conditions which is or are less favourable to him`
  line `than that or those to which he is entitled immedi ately before such deputation.`
  line `( 4 ) For the purposes of this section, an institution shall be deemed to be substantially owned by the`
  line `Bank if in the capital of the institution the Bank has not less than forty per cent, share.`
  line `Explanation. — The word “ capital ” means, in relation to the Unit Trust, the initial capital of the Trust.]`
  line `55. [ Reports by the Bank ]. — Omitted by the Reserve Bank ( Transfer to Public Ownership ) Act, 1948`
  line `(62 of 1948), s. 7 and the Schedule ( w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `56. [ Power to require declaration as to ownership of registered shares ]. — Omitted by s. 7 and the`
  line `Schedule, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `1. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.”.`
  line `2. Sub - section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 61 of 1981, s. 61 and the Second Schedule, for section 54 (w.e.f. 12 - 7 - 1982).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 24 of 1955, s. 10 (w.e.f. 8 - 5 - 1955).`
  line `5. The words “by or” omitted by Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 26 - 12 - 1960).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 58 of 1968, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 1969).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 52 of 1975, s. 20, for sub - section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 16 - 2 - 1976).`
