  line 61
  line `57. Liquidation of the Bank. — ( 1 ) Nothing in the 1 [Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)] shall apply to`
  line `the Bank and the Bank shall not be placed in liquidation save by order of the 2 [Central Government] and`
  line `in such manner as 3 [it may direct].`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 [57A. Powers of Bank not to apply to International Financial Services Centre. — Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the powers exercisable by the Bank under`
  line `this Act, —`
  line `( a ) shall not extend to an International Financial Services Centre set up under sub - Section ( 1 ) of`
  line `Section 18 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005);`
  line `( b ) shall be exerci sable by the International Financial Services Centres Authority established under`
  line `sub - Section ( 1 ) of Section 4 of the International Financial Services Centres Authority Act, 2019, in so`
  line `far as regulation of financial products, financial services and financ ial institutions that are permitted in`
  line `the International Financial Services Centres are concerned.]`
  line `58. Power of the Central Board to make regulations. — ( 1 ) The Central Board may, with the`
  line `previous sanction of the 2 [Central Government], 6 [by notification in the Official Gazette,] make`
  line `regulations consistent with this Act to provide for all matters for which provision is necessary or`
  line `convenient for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular without prejudice to the generalit y of the foregoing provision, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `( f ) the manner in which the business of the Central Board shall be transacted, and the procedure`
  line `to be followed at meetings thereof;`
  line `( g ) the conduct of business of Local Boards and the delegation to such Boards of powers and`
  line functions;
  line `( h ) the delegation of powers and functions of the Central Board 8 *** to Deputy Governors,`
  line `Directors or officers of the Bank;`
  line `( i ) the formation of Committees of the Central Board, the delegation of powers and functions of`
  line `the Central Board to such Committees, and the conduct of business in such Comm ittees;`
  line `( j ) the constitution and management of staff and superannuation funds for the officers and`
  line `servants of the Bank;`
  line `( k ) the manner and form in which contracts binding on the Bank may be executed;`
  line `( l ) the provision of an official seal of the Bank and t he manner and effect of its use;`
  line `( m ) the manner and form in which the balance - sheet of the Bank shall be drawn up and in which`
  line `the accounts shall be maintained;`
  line `( n ) the remuneration of Directors of the Bank;`
  line `( o ) the relations of the scheduled banks with th e Bank and the returns to be submitted by the`
  line `scheduled banks to the Bank;`
  line `( p ) the regulation of clearing - houses for the 9 [banks (including post office savings banks)];`
  line `10 [( pp ) the regulation of fund transfer through electronic means between the banks or be tween the`
  line `banks and other financial institutions referred to in clause ( c ) of section 45 - I, including the laying`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1957, s. 5, for “Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913)” (w.e.f. 8 - 6 - 1957).`
  line `2. Subs. by the M.O. 1937, for “G.G. in C.”.`
  line `3. Subs. by ibid., for “h e may direct”.`
  line `4. Sub - section ( 2 ) omitted by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 50 of 2019, s. 33 and the second Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 10 - 2020).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 6 (w.e.f. 30 - 12 - 1988).`
  line `7. Clauses ( a ) to ( e ) omitted by Act 62 of 1948, s. 7 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1 - 1 - 1949).`
  line `8. The words “to the Governor, or” omitted by Act 54 of 1953, s. 8 (w.e.f. 30 - 12 - 1953).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 6, for “the scheduled banks” (w.e.f. 30 - 12 - 1988).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 21 o f 2000, s. 94 and the Fourth Schedule (w.e.f. 9 - 6 - 2000).`
