obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line 62
  line `down of the conditions subject to which banks and other financial institutions shall participate in such`
  line `fund transfers, the manner of such fund transfers and the rights and obligations of the participants in`
  line `such fund transfers;]`
  line `( q ) the circumstances in which, and the conditions and limitations subject to which, the value of`
  line `any lost, stolen, mutilated or imperfect currency note of the Gover nment of India or bank note may be`
  line refunded;
  line `1 [( qa ) the remuneration and other allowances payable to Members of the Monetary Policy`
  line `Committee under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 45ZD;`
  line `( qb ) the functions of the Secretary under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 45ZG;`
  line `( qc ) the procedure, manner of conducting of meetings and related matters of the Monetary Policy`
  line `Committee under sub - section ( 12 ) of section 45ZI;`
  line `( qd ) the particulars and the frequency of publication of document under sub - section ( 2 ) of section`
  line 45ZJ;
  line `( qe ) the form and contents of the Monetary Policy Report to be published under sub - section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 45ZM;] and`
  line `( r ) generally, for the efficient conduct of the business of the Bank.`
  line `2 [( 3 ) Any regulation made under this section shall have effect from such earlier or later date as may`
  line `be specified in the regulation.`
  line `( 4 ) Every regulation shall, as soon as may be after it is made by the Central Board, be, forwarded to`
  line `the Central Government and that Government shall cause a copy of the same to be laid before e ach House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive ses sions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation, or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall,`
  line `thereafter, have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; s o, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.]`
  line `3 [( 5 )] Copies of all regulations made under this section shall be available to the public on payment.`
  line `4 [ 58A. Protection of action taken in good faith. — ( 1 ) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or the Bank or any other person in respect of anything which is`
  line `in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or in pursuance of any order, regulation or`
  line `direction made or given thereunder.`
  line `( 2 ) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or the Bank for any`
  line `damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `under this Act or in pursuance of any order, regulation or direction made or given thereunder.]`
  line `5 [CHAPTER V`
  line `P ENALTIES`
  line `58B. Penalties. — ( 1 ) Whoever in any application, declaration, return, statement, information or`
  line `particulars made, re quired or furnished by or under or for the purposes of any provisions of this Act, or`
  line `any order, regulation or direction made or given thereunder or in any prospectus or advertisement issued`
  line `for or in connection with the invitation by any person, of deposi ts of money from the public wil fully`
  line `makes a statement which is false in any material particular knowing it to be false or willfully omits to`
  line `make a material statement shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `years and sha ll also be liable to fine.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2016, s. 223 (w.e.f. 27 - 6 - 2016).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 51 of 1974, s. 24 (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `3. Sub - section ( 3 ) renumbered as sub - section ( 5 ) thereof by s. 24, ibid. (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 197 4).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 26, ibid. (w.e.f. 13 - 12 - 1974).`
