obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line 64
  line `amount of deposit received by such person in contravention of that secti on, or two thousand rupees,`
  line `whichever is more, or with both:`
  line `Provided that in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be mentioned in the`
  line `judgment of the court, the imprisonment shall not be less than one year and the fine shall not be less than`
  line `one thousand rupees.`
  line `( 5B ) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 29 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974), it shall be lawful for Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class to impose a`
  line `sentence of the fine in excess of the limit specified in that section on any person convicted under`
  line `sub - section ( 5A ).]`
  line `( 6 ) If any other provision of this Act is contravened of if any default is made in complying with any`
  line `other requirement of this Ac t or of any order, regulation or direction made or given or condition imposed`
  line `thereunder, any person guilty of such contravention or default shall be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to 1 [one lakh rupees] and where a contravention or default is a cont inuing one, with further fine`
  line `which may extend to 2 [ten thousand rupees] for every day, after the first, during which the contravention`
  line `or default continues.`
  line `58C. Offences by companies. — ( 1 ) Where a person committing a contravention or default referred to`
  line `i n section 58B is a company, every person who, at the time the contravention or default was committed,`
  line `was in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as`
  line `well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the contravention or default and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub - section shall render any such person liable to punishment`
  line `if he proves that the contravention or default was committed without his knowledge or that he had`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the contravention or default.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the same was committed with the consent or connivance of,`
  line `or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary, or other officer or`
  line `employee of the company, such director, manager, secretary, other officer or employee shall also be`
  line `deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line `Explanation 1. — Any offence punishable under this Act shall be deemed to have been committed at`
  line `the place where the registered office or the principal place of business, as the case may be, in India, of the`
  line `company is situated.`
  line `Explanation 2. — For the purpose of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “ a company ” means any body corporate and includes a corporation, a non - banking institution,`
  line `a firm, a co - operative society or other association of individuals;`
  line `( b ) “ director ”, in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
  line `58D. Application of section 58B barred. — Nothing contained in section 58B shall apply to, or in`
  line `respect of, any matter dealt with in section 42.`
  line `58E. Cognizance of offences. — ( 1 ) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `th is Act except upon a complaint in writing made by an officer of the Bank, generally or specially`
  line `authorised in writing in this behalf by the Bank, and no court other than that of a Metropolitan Magistrate`
  line `or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class or a co urt superior thereto shall try any such offence:`
  line `3 [Provided that in respect of any offence punishable under sub - section ( 5A ) of section 58B, a`
  line `complaint in writing may also be made by an officer of the State Government, generally or specially`
  line `authorised in writing in this behalf by that Government.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 142 for “ two thousand rupees ” (w.e.f. 9 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 142, ibid., for “one hundred rupees” (w.e.f. 9 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `3. Added by Act 1 of 1984, s. 12 (w.e.f. 15 - 2 - 1984).`
