obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line 65
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) a`
  line `Magistrate may, if he see reason so to do, dispense with the personal attendance of the officer of the Bank`
  line `filing the complaint, but the Magistrate may in his discretion, at any stage of the proceedings, direct the`
  line `personal attendance of the complainant.`
  line `58F. Application of fine. — A Court imposing any fine under this Act may direct that the whole or`
  line `any part thereof sh all be applied in, or towards payment of, the costs of the proceedings.]`
  line `1 [ 58G. Power of Bank to impose fine. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 58B, if`
  line `the contravention or default of the nature referred to in section 58B is committed by a non - banking`
  line `financial company, the Bank may impose on suc h non - banking financial company —`
  line `( a ) a penalty not exceeding 2 [twenty - five thousand]; or`
  line `( b ) where the contravention or default is under sub - section ( 4A ) or clause ( a ) or clause ( aa ) of`
  line `sub - section ( 5 ) of section 58B, a penalty of 3 [ten lakh ] rupees or twice the amount involved in such`
  line `contravention or default, where the amount is quantifiable, whichever is more; and where such`
  line `contravention or default is a continuing one, further penalty which may ex tend to 4 [one lakh] rupees`
  line `for every day, after the first, during which the contravention or default continues.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purpose of imposing penalty under sub - section ( 1 ), the Bank shall serve a notice on the`
  line `non - banking financial company requiring it t o show cause why the amount specified in the notice should`
  line `not be imposed as a penalty and a reasonable opportunity of being heard shall also be given to such`
  line `non - banking financial company.`
  line `( 3 ) Any penalty imposed by the Bank under this se ction shall be payable within a period of thirty`
  line `days from the date on which notice issued by the Bank demanding payment of the sum is served on the`
  line `non - banking financial company and, in the event of failure of the non - banking financial company to pay`
  line `the sum within such period, may be levied on a direction made by the principal civil court having`
  line `jurisdiction in the area where the registered office or the head office of the non - banking financial`
  line `company is situated:`
  line `Provided that no such direction shall be made, except on an application made by an officer of the`
  line `Bank authorised in this behalf, to by the principal civil court.`
  line `( 4 ) The court which makes a direction under sub - section ( 4 ), shall issue a certificate specifying the`
  line `sum payable by the non - banking financial company and every such certificate shall be enforceable in the`
  line `same manner as if it were a decree made by the court in a civil suit.`
  line `( 5 ) No complaint shall be filed against any non - banking financial company in any court of law`
  line `pertaining to any c ontravention or default in respect of which any penalty has been imposed by the Bank`
  line `under this section.`
  line `( 6 ) Where any complaint has been filed against a non - banking financial company in a court in respect`
  line `of contravention or default of the nature referred to in section 58B, no proceedings for imposition of`
  line `penalty against that non - banking financial company shall be taken under this section.]`
  line `59. [ Amendment of Act 3 of 1906 (Repealed) ]. — Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1937`
  line `(20 of 1937 ), s. 3 and the Second Schedule ( w.e.f. 14 - 4 - 1937).`
  line `60. [Repeals]. — Rep. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid. ( w.e.f. 14 - 4 - 1937).`
  line `61. [ Amendment of section II, Act VII of 1913 ]. — Rep. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid. ( w.e.f.`
  line `14 - 4 - 1937).`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 1997, s. 11 (w.e.f. 9 - 1 - 1997).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 143 for “ five thousand” (w.e.f. 9 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 143, ibid., for “ five lakh” (w.e.f. 9 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 143, ibid., for “twenty - five thousand” (w.e.f. 9 - 8 - 2019).`
